title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, mustard and onion.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets and boil in water 8 minutes. Meanwhile, melt cheese and milk together in a small saucepan. Drain cauliflower and put into a casserole dish. Pour melted cheese and milk over cauliflower. In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Stir cracker crumbs into butter gradually. Keep adding crumbs until butter absorbs, no more. Spread crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Can be made ahead and baked just before serving.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt until blended. Stir in scalded milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof pan.
Pour hot water into a larger pan so level of water is even with the level of the custard, as you put the custard dish into the pan of water while it is baking.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of the custard.
Bake in the 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until when you put a knife in the center and it comes out clean.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan. Gradually add milk, stirring until blended.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks, add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and butter.
Spoon into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar 1 minute.
Gradually add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar, slowly beating until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Let oleo or butter soften, also cream cheese.
Mix together well.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Mix spices together in a large Ziploc bag.
Wash chicken and sprinkle generously with spices.
Cover with foil and bake until almost done at 350°.
Then uncover and finish roasting.
If meat begins getting dry, use a little margarine.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli just until frost is out; drain.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix in Velveeta cheese cubes and water chestnuts.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with softened margarine; put on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add stick oleo.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 well beaten eggs slowly.
Mix well.
In large bowl, place 1 package small colored marshmallow plus cherries, cut up; add nuts.
Dust powdered sugar on wax paper.
Line 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan with paper.
Press mixture on paper and refrigerate until hard.
Cut in dainty size pieces.
Keeps well.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar.
Keep in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown meats and onions in skillet; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well.
Place in a 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kraut slaw or salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Cover; let marinate in refrigerator 24 hours.
Keeps well for 10 days or more.

title: vegetable trio
directions: Place all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat. Cover and cook 17 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Stir occasionally.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in a medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish, if desired.

title: simply delicious pork chops
directions: Arrange chops in single layer in a baking dish. In small bowl, combine oil, catsup, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce. Spread half of this over chops. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°. Turn chops; spread remaining mix. Bake 30 minutes more uncovered. Chops can be grilled using mix for basting, but double the sauce amount.

title: shawn's cowboy dip
directions: Brown and season hamburger meat.
Cut cheese into chunks and place in double boiler on medium heat.
Stir occasionally for about 8 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and seasonings while gradually stirring.
Cook on medium heat until dip is melted and hot.
Don't forget to keep stirring.

title: chicken birds
directions: Wrap chicken breasts with ham and bacon.
Lay in baking dish. Mix together soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam spray.
Sprinkle chopped pecans in bottom of bowl.
Dip each biscuit in butter and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Lay biscuit in pan, each biscuit overlapping the first. Bake 25 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies until they look like dirt.
Set aside.
Cream margarine with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk as directed on package.
Add to cream cheese mixture and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies, pudding mixture, cookies, pudding mixture, etc., ending with cookies on top.
Do this in a flower pot and put a silk flower in the middle and add a few gummy worms. Cute and good for much conversation.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo until tender.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce and stir; add 1/2 cheese.

title: ruby red frosty punch(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Mix fruit juices and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into punch bowl or large container.
Add chilled ginger ale and sherbet.
Serve immediately.

title: old fashioned doughnuts
directions: Beat in large bowl, eggs, sugar and shortening for 1 1/2 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add 2 cups flour mixture to egg mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in remaining flour mixture.
Chill dough for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Roll dough out on floured surface.
Cut with floured cutter.
Fry at 375° until brown, turning over once. Put on rack to cool.
Store in plastic bags and freeze.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Fry like any pancake.
Quick and full of protein!

title: swiss steak
directions: Wipe steak with damp cloth and cut into serving portions.
Mix flour and seasonings.
Pound flour mixture into steak with meat pounder or the edge of heavy saucer.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; shape into 12 balls.
Brown in skillet.
Drain fat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes, turning until meatballs are well glazed.
Serves 4.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt on cucumbers and onion and let stand for 2 hours.
Drain pickles.
Heat sugar, vinegar and celery seed until sugar melts.
Let set for 1/2 hour, stirring every 5 minutes.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, cool whip and milk.

title: breakfast pie
directions: In medium bowl, whisk together eggs and sour cream until blended.
Stir in bacon (or ham or sausage) and cheese.
Pour into greased pan (or a frozen deep-dish pie crust) and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in pan.
Cover with chili beans. Add shredded cheese.
Finally, add olives, onion and tomato.
Cook 10 minutes at 350°.

title: gooie butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg well.
Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut on top. Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl. Pour over cake. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, then cut into squares.
Store at room temperature.
These are very rich.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Combine margarine and cream cheese; cook over low heat until melted, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Combine spinach, artichoke hearts, cream cheese mixture, pepper and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Spoon in greased 7-inch dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for thirty minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate frosted cookies
directions: Cream the margarine or butter. Add egg yolk and mix. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in a greased 10 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet as evenly as possible. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese nuggets
directions: Combine cheese and butter; mix well.
Add flour, red pepper and pecans.
Stir until well mixed.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a casserole.
Use remaining onion rings to top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: german slaw(a handy salad to have around)
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, turmeric and spices.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Put in sterile jars.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps 6 months.

title: chicken and brown rice
directions: Cook chicken in hot oil in large electric skillet until browned. Remove chicken, keep warm. Add broth, dried soup mix and water to skillet, stir. Bring to boil. Stir in rice. Top with chicken; cover. Cook on low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and rice is tender. Let stand 5 minutes, stir. Makes 4 servings.

title: quick shrimp (scampi style)
directions: Have all ingredients within reach of stove.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and shred sweet potatoes.
Mix well pineapple and potatoes.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Cover with brown sugar. Cut butter and place on top of brown sugar.
Bake covered 20 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes or until done.

title: basic brown sauce
directions: Saute chopped onion in pan. Add flour and brown lightly. Slowly add the liquid, stirring to keep gravy smooth. Add rest of ingredients and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: In large bowl, stir together condensed milk and chocolate syrup.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in container.
Freeze about 6 hours.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: candied yams
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb cookies
directions: Mix rhubarb, water and raisins.
Mix remaining ingredients separately.
Mix all together.
Drop cookies.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lazy u chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together into a large bowl.
Mix margarine and cocoa in saucepan and bring to rapid boil.
Add to first mixture.
Pour water over mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Cook chicken in shortening over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Add onion rings, green peppers and garlic to skillet; cook and stir over medium heat until onion and peppers are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add chicken to sauce. Cover tightly; simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until thickest pieces are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruits, nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip last.
Pour into loaf pan or oblong Pyrex dish and freeze 6 to 8 hours.
When ready to serve, let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Slice or cut into squares and serve.
This recipe may also be used as a dessert, if desired.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix dry milk and Nestle Quik together with powdered confectioners sugar and Cremora.
Store in a tight container.
Mix 4 tablespoons mixture to 8 ounces hot water.

title: sparkling ale punch
directions: Blend cranberry juice, sugar and fruit juices.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and pudding according to package directions. Crumble cooled, baked cake.
Layer half of cake crumbs in bowl. Top with 1/2 each of pie filling, pudding, pineapple, bananas and nondairy whipped topping.
Repeat layers, using remaining 1/2 each of the ingredients.
Garnish with coconut, pecans and cherries, if you wish.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Use blade 3 chopper.
Place all ingredients in large boiler and cook until onions and cucumbers are tender.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring with wire whisk to remove lumps. Add oil, water and next 2 ingredients, stirring until smooth. Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat together egg, sugar, milk and shortening.
Set aside. Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to first mixture.
If batter is too soft to handle, add more flour.
Chill dough thoroughly.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and mix thoroughly.
Beat in flavorings and rind.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured ring pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt shortening in baking pan.
Coat bottom with oil.
Add remaining shortening and remaining ingredients to corn meal mix. Mix and pour in hot pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 9 to 10 servings.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Mix milk and sugar together; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Dissolve the Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water; add to milk and sugar mixture.
Add sour cream and vanilla and beat until smooth. Divide into three portions.
Mix one package of jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water (no cold water).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until completely set; add 1/3 of milk mixture and allow to set completely.
Repeat with other colors of jello with milk mixture in between and ending with a layer of jello.
Allow to set completely after each layer.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix soda and flour. Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat in mashed bananas. Add flour and soda mixture.
Mix well. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: confetti appetizers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours. Spread cut side of each muffin half with 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Place muffins on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Cut each muffin half into 4 wedges. Serve warm.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all together and pour in freezer and finish filling up with milk.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Use 9 inch pie tin.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together and let set for short while.
Fry.
Very good!

title: mint bonbon cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in muffin tins.
Cool; cut out centers.
Fill with vanilla ice cream. Pour 1 tablespoon creme de menthe over each one.
Serve immediately.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves.
Add baking soda and stir.
Pour mixture over popcorn and stir well.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir around, to cover well, every 15 minutes. Let cool and break apart.
Great snack!

title: hard candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to hard-boil stage.
Then add flavoring.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and let cool.
Twist the cookie sheet and the candy should crack.
Tap with a knife handle to make smaller pieces.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Store in decorative jar.
Great for gifts.

title: octoberfest ribs
directions: In a Dutch oven, layer all ingredients in the order listed. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 to 3 hours or until the ribs are tender. Yield: 6 servings.

title: kettle corn
directions: Heat oil in medium sized pan until hot.
Add popcorn and sprinkle all of the sugar over it.
Cover and shake CONTINUOUSLY until popped.

title: spaghetti amora
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain and blanch.
In a separate pan, heat the 2 cans of soup.
Add cheese.
Brown beef in skillet. Combine all ingredients and turn into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, shredded cheese and dry ranch dressing.
Form into a ball.
Roll in the pecans to cover.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix ketchup, chili sauce, horseradish and Tabasco sauce; shake well.
Arrange shrimp on lettuce.
Cover with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg yolk sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until light with electric beater.
Add sugar gradually, then add hot water, beating all the while.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Beat thoroughly.
Turn into angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until broom straw comes out clean.

title: hot chicken salad casserole(good)
directions: Combine half the chicken and next three ingredients on list. Spread on 6 slices of the bread.
Put slices into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with remaining chicken and last six slices of bread.
Mix evaporated milk, sour cream and dressing mix.
Pour on top of casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, top with the cheese and bake at 325° about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put in baking pan.
(If rhubarb is frozen, add 1 egg.)
Sift together the next 4 ingredients.
Cut butter in until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in beaten egg.
Spread over rhubarb mixture.
Shake pan to settle dough around rhubarb.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: In mixer, beat together cream cheese and Blue cheese.
Add green pepper, pimiento, garlic and jalapeno peppers.
Beat until like whipped cream.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread crushed nuts on a piece of waxed paper.
Spoon cheese out on top of nuts, shaping into roll and pushing nuts around it.
Keep refrigerated.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes; in large bowl.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in crock-pot/oven.
Place potatoes at sides of loaf. If potatoes are peeled, wrap in foil to help from darkening.
Put in oven at 375° for 1 hour in crock-pot on low 8 to 10 hours, on high 4 to 5 hours.

title: dip candy
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add other ingredients and mix well. Chill for 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls. Dip each ball in chocolate mixture of 1 (12 ounce) semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1 (4 ounce) package paraffin wax. Use toothpick to handle candy when dipping.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Prepare noodles, drain.
Add cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup.
Blend with noodles.
Add milk until noodles look creamy.
Stir in can of chicken.
Add Velveeta to taste.

title: day ahead brisket
directions: Brown brisket in a small amount of oil in Dutch oven.
Drain; sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with onion rings and celery.
Spoon chili sauce and 1/2 cup water around brisket.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender, basting occasionally over brisket. Refrigerate overnight.
Skim.
Slice brisket cross grain.
Heat. Serve on kaiser rolls with sauce.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in moderate oven at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: lemley favorite caramel corn
directions: Microwave on High 3 minutes. Stir it and then cook on High 2 minutes more.

Now add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and when this grows (peek at it through your window so it won't go all over your microwave), remove from your microwave and pour mixture over 6 quarts popped popcorn in a big grocery brown paper bag.
Mix the best you can shaking the bag.
Now return the bag to your microwave and cook on High 1 1/2 minutes. Take bag out and shake. Return for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out and shake until in big, yummy bites. So easy and really good.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together.
Fry in deep fat.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately to buttermilk vanilla mixture.
Spoon tablespoon sized drops of batter on slightly greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with a dash of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done; drain.
Cut up to bite size pieces. Cut up green pepper, onion, pickles, celery and eggs.
Mix together, then add salad dressing.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: nut cups
directions: Mix together and divide into
24 balls and shape around bottoms and sides of tiny muffin pans (don't melt margarine to mix).

title: basic sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Resift with baking powder and salt three times.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in flavoring.
Add dry ingredients with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat well.
Roll out and cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: honey-apple muffins
directions: Preheat
oven to 400°.	Grease twelve 2 3/4-inch muffin pan cups.
In
large
bowl
combine flour, wheat germ, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: potato candy(tastes like almond joy bars)
directions: Mix sugar, potatoes and coconut. Chill 1/2 hour. Melt chips and wax together. Roll the chilled ingredients into a small bowl. Place a nut in the center and dip in chocolate chip mixture. Place on waxed paper until dry. Can be frozen also.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat with spoon and pour into greased cake pans (3 layers). Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In skillet, cook meat until brown.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, sugar, tomato paste, garlic and spices.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix bean dip, sour cream and salad dressing in a bowl.
Spread on large serving platter.
Top with onion, tomato, bacon, cheese and olives.
Arrange chips around edge of platter.
Serve immediately.
May prepare bean dip mixture ahead and chill until serving time.
Yield:
25 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Place broccoli in a greased casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except for bread crumbs in a bowl.
Pour over broccoli.
Toss bread crumbs in melted butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli slaw salad
directions: Combine above.	Just before serving (or earlier if you like softer noodles) add 2 pkg. of Ramen noodles.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients and top with mayonnaise and sugar mixture.

title: zucchini pudding nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini, vanilla and dry pudding; mix lightly but well.
Add dry ingredients into first mixture. Fold in nuts and cherries.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: swedish crab souffle
directions: Cut bread in cubes; add onion flakes, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add milk to mayonnaise, mash eggs and add all together. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: orange-date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates. Stir until lukewarm.
Beat in by hand the oleo, egg, sugar and orange juice concentrate. Sift together dry ingredients, except nuts.
Fold dry ingredients into date mixture.
Add nuts and blend through.

Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick spray and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in loaf comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Turn out onto rack and cool completely.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add corn meal, then add beaten eggs, salt, vanilla, pineapple and coconut.
Bake at 325° until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Add peanut butter, eggs and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Shape in ball size or marble size.
Press with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: mary's fruit sauce
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together until thick and pale, about 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Great over fruit.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, covered in boiling, salted water, for approximately 15 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Combine potatoes, celery and green onion in large bowl.
Drizzle oil and vinegar dressing over top; toss lightly to mix.
Chill several hours to marinate.

title: veggie squares
directions: Rolls and cream cheese must be room temperature.
Press rolls into cookie sheet, pressing the seams together (make edge around cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes. Mix cheese, mayonnaise and dressing together.
Let dough cool, then spread mixture across the top.
Cut up your favorite raw vegetables and place on top of mixture.
Press down on veggies with your hand. Refrigerate.
Enjoy!!!

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine butter, Karo syrup, baking soda, brown sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over 5-quarts of popped corn and peanuts.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs, one at a time.

Beat until fluffy. Add flour mixture alternately with bananas and liquid, beating well after each addition. Turn into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and cool, then remove from pan.
Allow to cool for several hours before slicing.

title: turkey reuben canapes
directions: On nonstick baking sheet, arrange bread.
Spread 3/4 teaspoon Russian dressing on each slice.
Top with 1 slice turkey, 1 1/2 teaspoons sauerkraut and 1 slice cheese.
Broil until heated through and cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 4.
Contains 167 calories, 8 gm fat and 268 mg sodium.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Place butter and onion in skillet and saute.
Add croutons and mix.
Place 1/2 of the onion and croutons in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with tomato slices (1/2-inch thick).
Repeat layers. Sprinkle with chopped basil.
Sprinkle with grated Havarti cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Parboil chicken.
Chop into pieces.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix with soup, sour cream and jalapenos.
Spray Pam or butter 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Using 1/4 to 1/2 of mixture combined with chicken, fill each tortilla and toothpick closed. Pour remaining creamy mixture over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 30 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons into hot frying oil. Fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with butter and maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix the tuna, chopped peppers, chopped onions and tomato sauce with the mayonnaise.
Boil macaroni elbows; drain water.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.
Finally serve with steak, lettuce and a tomato.

title: penuche
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine granulated sugar, brown sugar, cream, milk and butter; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugars dissolve and mixture comes to boiling.
Continue cooking to 236° (soft ball stage), stirring only as necessary to prevent sticking.
Mixture should boil gently over the entire surface.
Immediately remove from heat; cook, without stirring, to lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla.
Beat vigorously about 10 minutes or until mixture becomes very thick and starts to lose its gloss.
Quickly stir in nuts.
Immediately turn into buttered 8 x 4 x 2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Score into squares while warm; cut when firm. Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: classic rich bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups of flour, yeast, sugar and salt; mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until warm (120° to 130°); butter does not need to melt.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough.
Divide into 3 parts.
On lightly floured surface, roll or pat each third to a 14 x 7-inch rectangle.
Starting with shorter side, roll up tightly, pressing dough into roll with each turn.
Pinch edges and ends to seal.
Place in greased 8 x 4-inch bread pans.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pans; cool.

title: restaurant style buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and soda and salt in medium-sized bowl.	In another bowl mix egg, milk and cooking oil. Pour egg mixture into flour bowl.
Stir just enough to blend but do not overstir.
Batter should still be lumpy.
Pour 1/2 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased buttered griddle or heavy skillet.
Cook until golden brown and flip.
Makes approximately five 6-inch cakes.	I always double this recipe for my family of four.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Heat milk, syrup, butter, sugar and salt until warm and butter is almost melted.
In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Let sit five minutes.
Add warm milk mixture and 2 1/2 cups flour, beat well.
Add 2 1/2 cups wheat flour, beat about 4 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups wheat flour, turn out onto floured surface and knead until smooth, about 5 minutes, using rest of wheat flour.
Place dough in greased bowl, turn up, cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down, divide in half, shape into 2 balls.
Cover, let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves, place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Cover, let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut desired amount of potatoes in rings and boil.
In saucepan, melt 1 stick butter; add enough flour (gravy) and 1 can evaporated milk.
Mix that with drained potatoes.
Layer in baking dish potatoes and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: onion supper bread
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Prepare mix as directed.
Pour into greased pan.
Spread onion mix on top.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Mix cheese and sour cream and spoon on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: bob's red wine venison chili
directions: Brown venison in oil, add onions and peppers, brown stirring as meat cooks. Drain off fat.
Add bouillon, tomatoes, salt, sugar, peppers and chili powder. Cover and simmer at least 2 hours.
Add beans and wine simmer until heat through.
Serve with corn bread.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir. Sift together dry ingredients and add to chocolate mixture.
Stir well and pour into 8-inch greased pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: rolled ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, stirring after each addition.
Add flour last; mix well.
(Dough will be stiff, but sticky.)
Chill dough in refrigerator for several hours before rolling.
Take about 1/4 of the dough at a time and place on floured surface.
Knead a little flour into ball of dough before rolling.
Cut out cookies and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan crunchies
directions: Lightly oil a jelly roll pan and line with graham crackers. Melt butter in a medium saucepan. Add brown sugar and stir until mixture bubbles vigorously.
Add pecans and quickly spread over the graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or less. Cut along indentations of the crackers.
Leave in pan and freeze for 1 hour, uncovered.
Do not eliminate freezing because that is what makes these so crunchy.
Store in airtight container.

title: bierrolls
directions: Make yeast bread dough 2 hours before needed.
Let rise.
(May be made and refrigerated ahead of time.)
Shred or cut cabbage coarsely.
Cook cabbage and onions in a small amount of water; season to taste.
When tender, drain well.
Brown hamburger in skillet, breaking it apart as it browns.
Drain well and add to cabbage and onions.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Spray 8-inch square dish.
Mix all the ingredients and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple cheese crisp
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Arrange in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. (If apples are very dry, add 1/4 cup water to bottom of pan.)
Blend together butter, sugar and flour until crumbly. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 2/3 of the beef and add rest of the ingredients.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining beef.
Make a day ahead for better flavor.

title: spirited chocolate fondue
directions: In small heavy saucepan, combine morsels and evaporated milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in liqueur.
Serve warm with strawberries and cake cubes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Layer bread and ham.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt and pour over bread and ham.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9 pan.
Mix all other ingredients together. Pour into pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hardees' biscuits
directions: Mix and knead lightly.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain fish.
Remove bones and skin and flake fish.
Melt butter; blend in flour, then stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add fish, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cool.
Shape into croquettes.
Dip into egg and coat evenly.
Roll in potato chip crumbs coating evenly.
Deep fry at 365° until golden (a few minutes).

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Just before serving, add 4 bottles of 7-Up and red cake coloring.

title: buckeyes
directions: *Can use chocolate for making candy.

title: almond roca
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 10 x 15-inch foil lined pan and arrange a layer of soda crackers.

title: lemon mystery pudding(given to me 60 years ago by my 4-h club leader)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, lemon, milk and flour.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in buttered baking dish set in pan of warm water 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, taco seasoning and jalapeno pepper dip.
Spread on bottom of cookie sheet that has edges.
Combine chopped ingredients and sprinkle over sour cream mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: cannoli cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Mix cake per instructions; put in pan.
Mix well Ricotta, eggs, vanilla or almond and sugar.
Gently pour Ricotta mixture over cake and spread with a spoon.

title: remarkable multi bean soup
directions: Boil water in a large pot; add onions, beans, spices and honey.
Bring back to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in tomato sauce and paste.
Add green pepper.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 to 40 minutes until soup starts to thicken.
If you can feel the beans colliding with the spoon, it is not ready.
Cook until you can stir more smoothly.

title: canned okra
directions: Put okra in dishpan.
Pour salt and vinegar on top.
Add enough water to cover the okra.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Dip out okra with drain spoon to add to jars.
When jar is full, dip out liquid to cover okra.
Before frying okra, I always rinse okra with water to get some of the vinegar taste off.
Canning this way helps keep the okra firm.

title: zucchini alfredo
directions: Cut zucchini into long thin strips about 1/4 inch wide. In a large colander, toss the zucchini with salt, allow to drain for one hour, then rinse and drain. Pat dry. In a 12 inch skillet, cook zucchini and garlic in hot oil for about 2 or 3 minutes or until crisp-tender. Transfer mixture to a large bowl. In the skillet heat cream cheese and half and half until smooth, stir in parmesan, then add zucchini, heat through. Place in a serving dish, sprinkle with pepper, nutmeg and additional parmesan.

title: layered lemon crumb bars
directions: Combine Eagle Brand, lemon juice and rind; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add oatmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of oatmeal mixture on bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with lemon mixture.
Stir spices into remaining crumbs; sprinkle evenly over lemon layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove bone and mash salmon.
Beat eggs and add to salmon. Mix milk, flour and meal with salmon.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot cooking oil.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain excess grease.
Mix hamburger, soups and sour cream.
Cook noodles.
Layer hamburger mixture and noodles.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put the popped corn into a brown paper bag.
Put the oleo, brown sugar, corn syrup and vanilla in a 2-cup or larger microwave measuring cup.
Cook 2 minutes on High. Stir.
Cook another 2 minutes. Add the soda and salt.
Pour mixture over popcorn in bag. Shake well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High. Shake.
Microwave another 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and pour on 2 cookie sheets.

title: potatoes and peas
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Place in baking dish with oil and desired seasoning.
Preheat oven to 350°.
No lid.
Brown 1/2 hour.
Turn and brown 1/2 hour more.
Last 10 minutes, add peas.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together dry ingredients (except powdered sugar).
Combine all remaining ingredients (except powdered sugar) in a separate bowl.
Add liquid mixture to the dry mixture.
Stir carefully, just enough to blend all ingredients.

title: baked apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples into bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, cloves and lemon juice.
Mix and put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: sweet dills(they sure taste good.)
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, not a hard boil, for 1 minute.
Let cool to warm.
Drain off the brine from the dills and toss away.
Cut dills into slices. Replace in jar.
You can strain out spices or leave them and pour the warm syrup over dills in jar.
Store in refrigerator for 1 week, or use in a few days.
You can let sugar and vinegar dissolve before cooking.
When cooking syrup, take off burner before it comes to hard boil.
The second batch I made with old syrup, just add 2/3 cup vinegar, 1/2 cup sugar and more spices to old syrup.
Cook again; put in new jar of dills.
I buy dills already sliced.

title: oatmeal surprises
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Blend vanilla.
In separate bowl
sift
flour, baking powder and soda.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Stir in oats, coconut and cereal.
Drop by teaspoon on greased
baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly on baking sheets. Cool on racks.

title: steak burgundy
directions: Saute steak in oil until brown.
Add onions and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in carrots, wine, broth, mushrooms with the liquid and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer ten minutes longer.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened. Serve over rice.
Makes six servings.

title: curried chicken skillet supper
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken and sprinkle with pepper.
Coat an electric skillet with cooking spray.
Allow to heat to medium for 2 minutes. Add chicken to skillet.
Cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove chicken.
Drain on paper towels. Set aside.
Wipe skillet with paper towel and spray again. Add apple, onion, celery and garlic to skillet.

Cook at medium heat, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender. Stir in water, raisins, curry powder, orange rind and red pepper. Return chicken to skillet. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting chicken occasionally. Remove chicken to a serving platter and keep warm. Combine orange juice and cornstarch, stirring until blended.
Stir into skillet. Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute or until thick.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.

title: fruit and dumplings(serves 5)
directions: Pour reserved liquids into 4-cup measure; add enough water to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Stir in cornstarch, cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
Microwave uncovered on High 4 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until mixture boils and thickens.
Mix with fruits in round 8 x 1 1/2-inch dish.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; beat in eggs and cream and blend in bananas, vanilla and flour with salt and soda.
Pour into 10 x 5 x 3 1/2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cover with cloth when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Mix soup, sour cream, celery and pimento.
Grease a baking dish. Layer broccoli, then cheese, soup mixture, crackers and then more cheese.
Sprinkle with pepper. Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all together. Add milk and eggs last. Bake in greased aluminum cake pans.
Bake at 350° to 375° until done.

title: food haven gumbo
directions: Roux:
Use 1 1/2 cups of all purpose flour and blend into 1 1/2 cups hot oil or pork renderings to make dark brown roux (almost burned).
Stir all the time roux is cooking, about 30 minutes.

title: marilyn's injected turkey
directions: Mix liquids together well.
Inject turkey with juice mixture. Refrigerate overnight or 24 hours.

title: garlic dip
directions: In blender, whip ingredients until smooth (except vegetables). Refrigerate until serving.
Makes 8 servings; 20 calories per serving.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased muffins pans (2/3 full). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine ingredients and mix.
Serve with ice.

title: salmon and dill cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll formed cheese ball in pecans.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices and then into 1/4-inch dices.
Remove chorizo from casing and place in a large skillet. Cook and mash chorizo until lightly browned and fat has melted. Add diced potatoes and onions.
Cover and cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove lid.
With the back of spoon, press 4 indentions in mixtures.
Break an egg into each indention.
Cover and cook until eggs are set (about five minutes).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and combine the sugar,
baking powder, soda, flour, salt and spices.
Add eggs, salad
oil and pumpkin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: potato devine
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Spread into 9 x 13 baking pan.
Top with cereal and drizzle margarine over cereal. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: la-la's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in a ball and then in pecan nuts.
Or, place in a bowl and top with pecan nuts.
Spread or dip crackers.

title: babka (polish)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let it foam for about 5 minutes. Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add salt, grated orange rind and vanilla.
Add 1/2 of the flour and yeast mixture; beat well.

Add butter to the hot milk and when melted, add this mixture to the other part of dough and mix in the balance of the flour with a wooden spoon; beat for about 5 minutes, then add the fruit and nuts carefully.
Let rise until double in size; punch down; let rise again, then put into baking pan the size of an angel food pan and let rise until doubled.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350`°.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir together cornmeal, flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add beaten egg and melted margarine; stir until mixed, then add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Turn into greased 9 x 9-inch pan or into greased muffin pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden and done.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour in saucepan.
Slowly stir in milk.
Boil for 1 minute over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir half of mixture into egg yolks, then pour back into remaining pudding.
Boil another minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, cream cheese, bean dip, seasoning mix and Tabasco sauce.

title: white mountain icing
directions: Cook all
ingredients,	except	egg whites and vanilla. Cook until spins
thread;
pour	1/3
over
beaten egg whites. Cook until soft boil;
pour 1/3 over egg whites, beating after each addition.
Cook
remainder	until hard crack.
Repeat the same. Add vanilla.
This may be used on coconut, banana or any kind of cake.

title: seafoam kisses
directions: Combine sugars, salt and water in saucepan; boil until mixture spins a hard thread or a hard ball in cold water (255°).
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla; beat with mixer until mixture is stiff and will hold its shape.
Drop by spoon onto greased waxed paper.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix 3 cups of milk, 1/2 bowl of Cool Whip, cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix everything except pecans. Chill several hours or overnight. Spread chopped pecans on waxed paper and roll the cheese ball on it until coated. Chill completely before serving.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water, add pineapple with juice and whole berry cranberry sauce and mix well.
Add nuts if desired. Congeal.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in greased 2-quart baking dish.
In bowl, mix cream, mayonnaise, milk and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crackers and poppy seed and put over soup layer.
Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, baking powder, raisins, cinnamon, baking soda and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 4 small or 2 large loaves.

title: easy escabecce eggplants
directions: Wash eggplants and cut off stems.
Cut slices about 1/2-inch wide; (if eggplants are too big, cut in half lengthwise and then slice).

title: grande casserole
directions: Crumble chips to cover bottom of 9 x 12 - inch casserole dish.
Saute meat, onions, and taco mix.

title: super quick chili with cheese
directions: Prepare Velveeta as package directs.
Stir together; heat and serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and marshmallows in medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate in covered bowl or jar. Best if made 2 or 3 days ahead.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Bake until brown on top.

title: beef turnovers
directions: Combine roast beef, cream cheese, relish and onion in bowl; mix well.
Unroll crescent rolls, forming 8 squares.
Spoon equal portions of mixture in center of each square.
Fold up corners to enclose filling.
Seal edges.
Arrange in baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Mix together softened margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
If too thick to spread, add a little pineapple juice.
Slice bananas over this layer.
Cover with crushed pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with chopped nuts.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Shuck and silk corn.
Place on a 12-inch piece of wax paper. Spread margarine across corn.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll up in wax paper and place in microwave.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn once 1/2 way through cooking.

title: ground turkey breast basic mix
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Add other seasonings as desired.
You can use this mixture for burgers, meat loaf, meat balls or as you would for ground beef.

title: bacon bean salad
directions: Rinse kidney beans.
Quarter and thinly slice onion; thinly slice bell pepper.
Blend vinegar, sugar and salt in small pan; heat until sugar dissolves.
Set aside to cool.
Drain all beans; toss with onions, peppers, pepper and vinegar mix.
Pour in oil and toss again.
Just before serving, add bacon and toss again.

title: my pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla and beat.
Place in tube cake pan and bake at 275° for about 1 hour until done.

title: easy cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker on low for 2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and beat again.
Mix soda and salt with flour and mix in alternately with the milk.
Add nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Then add egg, milk and vanilla; beat until blended.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in remaining sugar.
Place about 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Top each cookie with kisses, then bake for an additional 2 minutes.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients in the water. Bring mixture to a boil, then simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with French bread.

title: baked chicken with garlic
directions: Wash fryer, place on rack in large shallow pan.
Sprinkle salt and garlic on both sides.
Put bags of butter on top of chicken and put small amount of water in pan.
Cook at 350°
for 1 hour or until golden brown, turning over one time.
Serve with rice.

title: easy cherry-pineapple cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with wrappings from oleo.
Pour canned pineapple with juice into baking dish.
Add pie filling a spoon at a time evenly over pineapple.
Add dry cake mix and smooth.
Pour melted margarine on top, then cover with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lye soap
directions: Melt grease and strain.
Let cool.
Pour water on lye; let cool, stirring until dissolved.
Add Borax to lye water and stir until dissolved.
Add this to the grease and stir 7 minutes.
Add ammonia and stir 3 minutes longer.
The more you stir, the whiter the soap.
(Any scrape grease can be used:
bacon drippings, grease from fish fries, etc.)
Let cool and set.
Cut into desired shapes. Do not use aluminum pans and use only wooden spoons to stir.

title: "po boys" delight
directions: Pat hamburger meat into bite size patties.
Place in glass baking dish and slice potatoes over meat.
Mix soup with small amount of water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over potatoes and meat. Cook in oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Place chicken in baking dish in single layer.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, sherry and mushrooms.
Spread soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve with noodles or whole wheat toast.
Equals 1 vegetable, 3 lean meats and 1 fat.

title: chicken rice dinner
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken, place in large skillet over medium heat and brown in oil.
Place rice in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion and garlic.
Top with mushrooms.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Pour over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until chicken and rice are done.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Partially thaw strawberries. Toss in bowl; add sliced bananas.
Add pie filling last.
Toss well.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: roast chicken with herbs and lemon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub juice from 1/2 lemon inside the chicken and sprinkle inside with salt and pepper.
Put melted butter or olive oil over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining salt and pepper.
Truss chicken, if desired.
Mix herbs and spices and sprinkle over chicken.
Roast, uncovered, for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally with pan juices.

title: garlic toast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread softened butter over 1 side of each slice of French bread.
Sprinkle garlic powder and cheese over butter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet until tops are golden brown, about 7 minutes.
Turn slices, spread with butter and sprinkle with garlic powder and cheese.
Bake 7 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and completely cover a flat plate.
Pour cocktail sauce, covering all of the cream cheese.
Sprinkle crab meat over sauce. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Combine with soups in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with Velveeta cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Place Tater Tots evenly on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until cheese is bubbly and Tater Tots are brown.

title: lemon-blueberry muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Combine eggs with next 3 ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Spray muffin tins with cooking spray or use bake cups.
Spoon in batter, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: simple pear salad
directions: Arrange lettuce and kale leaves.
Top with pear halves.
Place 1 tablespoon mayonnaise on top of each half.
Sprinkle
each half with 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan, pretzels, melted margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Add rest of butter and cheese.
Prepare instant potatoes according to package directions, if using instead of fresh potatoes.
May need to add more salt and butter to taste.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer onion, noodles and potatoes; repeat, ending up with last 3 noodles.
Top with remaining onion.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Put tea bags in 2 cups boiling water; leave until cooled.
Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Spoon frozen mixture into glass (4 tablespoons to 8 ounce glass) and cover with 7-Up.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, oil and chocolate chips together. Set aside while chopping nuts. Put chopped nuts in bowl. By teaspoonfuls, roll candy mixture in chopped nuts.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add warm water and knead until dough is soft, but not sticky.
Stretch and pat dough until thin.
Tear off 1 piece at a time; poke a hole in the middle and drop into kettle of sizzling hot lard or cooking oil.
Brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: greek bisquit cookies
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and cream well again.
Add the rest of the ingredients with enough flour to make a nice soft dough and knead for a while, then shape and bake in 350° oven until lightly brown (on greased cookie sheet).

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine water, milk, sugar, egg and margarine and mix well. Add flour 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition. Spoon mixture into greased muffin cups.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Batter can be stored for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant.
Beat remaining ingredients with rotary beater until smooth.
Heat fat or oil (1-inch deep) to 375° in large skillet.
Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip slices into batter letting excess drip into bowl.
Fry in hot fat until golden brown, turning once.
Drain.
If desired, salt to taste. Yields four servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Let stand 4 hours in a covered container with cracked ice.
Drain well; combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over the cucumber mix.
Heat to boiling point. Seal at once in hot jars.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Sprinkle liquid smoke over meat.
Combine celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt; rub in both sides.
Place in foil, seal and refrigerate overnight.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Slowly add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla.
Combine crackers, nuts and baking powder.
Fold gently into egg whites.
Pour into well-greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: For roux, in a large, heavy saucepan combine flour and oil until smooth.
Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook and stir about 15 minutes until roux is dark, reddish brown.
Stir in onion, celery, garlic, black pepper and red pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring often.
Gradually stir in hot chicken broth and sausage.
Add chicken.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: cabbage soup(lo-cal and tastes great)
directions: Boil the broth; add cabbage for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and onions; cook until tender, then add the milk and Butter Buds. (The original recipe calls for heavy cream and real butter.)

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: huckleberry muffins(makes 12 muffins)
directions: Break 1 egg into 1 cup measuring cup.
Fill with milk.
Beat egg and milk mixture and add oil.
Sift dry ingredients together. Put huckleberries into flour mixture to coat them individually with flour.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients and mix but not too thoroughly.
Put in greased muffin pan and bake at 400° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sin pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts.
Spread in pan (9 x 13-inch). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Let set until thick; spread over cream cheese.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill

title: banana-pineapple pudding
directions: Combine pineapple, mandarin oranges and peaches.
(Be sure all fruit is drained well.)
Add apple chunks.

title: mom's salad dressing cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done.
When I make this I usually double the recipe.

title: melting moments
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cornstarch.
Blend in butter until soft dough is formed.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned at edges.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.
Very good.
After they are cool, ice.

title: mom's famous onion rings
directions: Slice onions and use outer rings.
Put in ice water.
Have hot oil ready to deep-fry rings.
Dip onion rings into buttermilk, then flour mixture and then back into buttermilk and then flour, then drop into deep fryer until golden brown.

title: banana nut raisin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and allspice together; add to butter and sugar.
Add raisins and nuts.
(Heat raisins in pan over slow heat, stirring constantly; will prevent them from sinking to bottom of batter.)
Add mashed bananas and bake in tube pan at 275° until done.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put water and butter in a pan and bring to a boil.
Boil until butter melts and cool.
Add flour and boil again for 1 minute and cool again.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
With a spoon, drop on a cookie sheet that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix.
Last, stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonful and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute vegetables in hot oil until golden brown.
Add tomatoes and spices; simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook ravioli following directions.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: eleanor's bran muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine All Bran cereal, Shredded Wheat biscuits, and boiling water.
In another mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar and then beat in eggs.
Add bran ingredients to creamed mixture;
stir well.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk; mix well.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen muffins.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat 1 cup water and margarine until they boil.
Add flour and stir until a ball forms (almost immediately).
Let cool.
Beat in 4 eggs, one at a time.
Spread mixture in a glass 9 x 13-inch pan with a little of the dough mixture up the sides of the pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
It will be puffy, then let cool.
Mix 3 packages of the pudding with the milk; pour in prepared crust. Top with Cool Whip and drizzle Hershey syrup on top and nuts.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and make into a smooth paste.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Beat some of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return rest to saucepan, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add crabmeat, parsley, salt, nutmeg, cayenne pepper, soft crumbs and 1/4 cup dry crumbs.
Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes.
Shape into cakes; dip into egg yolk mixture.
Coat completely with remaining crumbs.
Saute until brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced tea(great for gift giving)
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in container of choice for gift giving.

title: macaroni and vegetable salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, bouillon and garlic powder.
Mix well and set aside.
In a 4 or 5-quart bowl, layer salad greens, macaroni, peas, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Stir dressing and spread evenly over salad.
Top with bacon bits. Cover and chill for 6 hours or overnight.
Toss to serve.
Makes 11 cups.

title: burt's beef stew
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, cook bacon until light brown. Combine the flour and black pepper in a bowl; dip the meat in the flour mixture to coat completely.
Brown coated meat in bacon fat, turning often.
Add a little vegetable oil, if needed.
Add onion and garlic and brown both a little.
Add tomato sauce, beef broth, wine, bay leaf and thyme.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, celery, then potatoes and mushrooms.
Cook, covered, another 30 minutes, or until vegetables are tender. Serve with hot Italian bread, a large salad, fine wine and good friends.

title: tuna-rice pie
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cook broccoli; drain well and set aside.
Combine rice and egg; mix well.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish; set aside.
Combine soup and sauce in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broccoli, mushrooms and tuna.
Pour into rice shell; cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with olive slices.

title: sweet potatoes praline
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs, salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except pecans.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in slow cooking pot over medium heat of range unit.
Remove excess grease.

title: margee's spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into molasses mixture.
Chill 3 hours.
On floured surface, roll out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: roasted chicken radicchio tacos
directions: Combine chicken and rice.
Use 2 heads of raddicchio leaves and put filling in each leaf.
Roll, tying with the chives.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti; drain and set aside.
Saute beef; drain excess fat. Mix with Provolone, salami, chopped eggs and 1 cup of the sauce. Put another cup of the sauce in large casserole.
Add a layer of ziti, sprinkle with a little of the Parmesan.
Add a layer of meat, Provolone cheese mixture, then a layer of sauce.
Sprinkle with a little more Parmesan.
Alternate layers until all is used. Top with remaining sauce and the rest of the Parmesan.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove cover last 10 minutes. Serves 4 generously.

title: potato casserole
directions: Warm the Cheez Whiz and sour cream together on the stove. Layer this mixture over the sliced potatoes in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans thoroughly, saving liquid.
In 1 quart casserole, combine undiluted soup and 1/3 cup bean liquid.
Mix in beans and half the onions.
Bake in moderate oven, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until sauce is bubbling.
Top with the remaining onions. Continue baking 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chiffon style cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Chill until it begins to set, then whip and fold into whipped cream. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill until set.

title: bavarian cabbage chowdercreston, iowa
directions: Brown meat in large heavy pan.

title: driftwood restaurant horseradish salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; cool.
Add pineapple and chill until slightly congealed; add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set. Makes 8 servings.

title: tart chicken salad with sour-cream dressing
directions: In a heavy 2 to 3-quart pot, combine the chicken, onion and 1 teaspoon of the salt.
Cover with about 1 1/2 quarts of cold water and bring to a boil uncovered over high heat, skimming off the fat and scum as it rises to the surface.
Partially cover the pan, reduce the heat to low and simmer about 10 minutes, or until the chicken is tender.
Remove the chicken from the pot and with a small, sharp knife, remove and discard the skin and cut the meat away from the bones.
Cut the chicken meat into strips about 1/2-inch wide and combine them in a large mixing bowl with the pickles, potatoes and eggs.
Sprinkle with the remaining teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of white pepper.
In a small bowl, beat together the mayonnaise and sour cream and stir half of it into the salad.
Taste for seasoning.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put water, cornstarch and sugar in pan.
Cook until clear and thick.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift flour twice and add gradually to first 4 ingredients.
Add mashed bananas.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers.
Mix all ingredients and let come to a good boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Set for 5 minutes.
Add 1 bottle Certo. Pour in jars and seal.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Either butter the 9 slices of bread or dip each slice in melted butter.
Cut off crusts and save.
Cut remaining bread in cubes.

title: savory pork
directions: In bowl, pour 3 tablespoons soy sauce over pork.
On plate, combine sugar and flour and roll pork cubes in sugar-flour mixture.
Pour oil in wok or skillet and preheat, uncovered.
Add 1/2 of pork and stir-fry 3 minutes or until browned.
Remove or push up sides.
Add remaining pork and stir-fry.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove pork.
In small bowl, mix cold water and cornstarch.
Stir slowly in meat drippings.
Add remaining soy sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Add meat and walnuts.
Cook 3 minutes, then serve.

title: pulled pork barbecue
directions: Rub pork with 1 teaspoon chili powder and the garlic powder; place in baking pan.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until pork is well browned and juices run clear, 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch slices; shred slices into bite-size pieces with fork.
Spray medium saucepan with cooking spray; heat over medium heat until hot.
Saut onion and garlic until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except Equal, salt, pepper and buns to saucepan; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until a medium sauce consistency, 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in Equal.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir pork into sauce; cook until hot, 2 to 3 minutes.
Spoon mixture into buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cincinnati-style chili
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onions until brown and onions are tender.
Drain.
Stir in chili powder, salt, tomatoes, beans and tomato sauce.
Break up tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until desired consistency, about 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Spoon about 3/4 cup beef mixture over 1 cup spaghetti.
Sprinkle each serving with 1/4 cup shredded cheese.

title: lazy maple rolls
directions: In 8-inch round pan, melt in oven the first 3 ingredients. Sprinkle with nuts.
Combine the sugar and cinnamon.
Dip both sides of dough in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Put rolls in pan. Bake 18 to 22 minutes at 375°.
Cool 1 minute.
Turn onto wax paper.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Sift flour and salt together into bowl. In a separate bowl, cream peanut butter, butter and vanilla together; gradually add brown sugar, beating until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Blend in flour.
Stir in peanuts.
Spoon batter into greased 8-inch square baking pan; spread evenly.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then cut into squares. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: beef ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Score ribs on both sides between bones. Lay ribs in bottom of roasting pan with lid.
Combine coffee, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and bake 2 hours, until ribs are browned and tender, another 20 minutes or so.
Ribs may be turned over after 10 minutes to brown other side.

title: flapjack
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch cake tin.
Cut butter into 4 parts and melt in saucepan with sugar and syrup; stir well with wooden spoon.
Remove from heat and add oats; stir well.
Spoon mixture into cake tin and put into oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven and leave to cool for 25 minutes.
Cut into 8 or 12 pieces; lift out and leave until cold.
Store in airtight container.

title: corn stuffed zucchini
directions: In skillet, fry onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: mom's shepherd pie
directions: Cook hamburg over medium heat (so it does not really brown) with cut up onions.
Pour off fat and liquid; set aside.
Mix mashed potatoes with cheese, egg, salt and pepper to taste.
In deep ovenproof dish, layer hamburg, onion mixture and creamed corn. Top with potato mixture.
Cook in oven at 300° until bubbly and potato topping is dry and crisp.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: anna's favorite cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt. Mix well until blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Place graham crust tin on a baking sheet (to prevent spills). Pour in cream cheese mixture. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix.
Refrigerate until you can shape it. Then roll in pecans.

title: short bread
directions: Work sugar and butter together. Gradually add flour until well blended. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cut in 2-inch squares while hot. Cool and store in airtight container.
Melts in your mouth.

title: super chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a large baking dish.
Mix soup and cream in a bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Combine stuffing mix and chicken broth in a bowl.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: ham and swiss roll-ups
directions: Mix dip, cream cheese and chopped olives.
Chill for 1 hour. Spread half of mixture evenly on ham slices; top with cheese slices.
Spread remaining mixture on cheese, line up whole olives along one side (long side) of each piece of cheese.
Roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill at least 2 hours.
Cut each roll into 1/2-inch slices.
Yield: about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add rest of ingredients, except for nuts.
Line pan with wafers; pour mixture into pan and top with nuts.
Keep in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add cold water, sugar, syrup and lemon juice until partially jelled. Add other ingredients and pour into oiled mold.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, chicken, water chestnuts, mushrooms and onion. Add 1 cup cheese and the mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt margarine and crushed crackers together and top the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and slightly browned.

title: tuna crunch
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup Chinese noodles.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine remaining noodles and all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle reserved noodles on top.
Bake for 5 minutes more.

title: easy dilled salmon cakes
directions: Put 1/2 cup of bread crumbs off to side.
Mix remaining ingredients and form into patties.
Coat patties with the 1/2 cup of crumbs.
Brown quickly in butter until crisp and golden brown. Serve with lemon.
Excellent with creamed peas and scalloped potatoes.

title: cheese squares
directions: Remove the crust from bread and cut into 1-inch squares.
In a double boiler, melt cheese and butter.
When creamy, fold in egg whites.
Dip cubes into mixture.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in plastic bag and store in freezer.
To serve, bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: spice macaroons(kryddermakroner)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Set by spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown around the edges.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. In mixing bowl combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat until thickened.
Spread over cake.
Spoon pie filling on top. Chill.

title: picante black-eyed peas
directions: Cook peas in a large saucepan. Saute pepper and onion in butter for 2 minutes. Add sauce. Stir into peas. Simmer until thick.

title: pineapple pizpizzen cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in tube pan for best results.
Bake at 300° until nicely brown.
Cake is moist.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup bread crumbs.
Drizzle 1/4 cup butter or oleo over crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients boil for 5 minutes on low.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and salt. Stir.
Pour over the popped corn. Cook for 1 hour at 200°.
Take out, lay on sheet and break apart.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients. Gradually stir in milk. Add oleo, stirring constantly; bring to boil over medium heat. Stir in next 3 ingredients. Toss with vegetables. Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with topping. Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: pam's sour orange pie filling or pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into baked pie crust, graham cracker crust or into dish (for a crustless pudding). Chill for a few hours.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine applesauce, sugars, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Add salt, baking soda and spices.
Slowly add flour; mix well. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: creamy carrot-nut mold
directions: Lightly oil mold with salad or cooking oil (not olive oil). Pour hot water over gelatin in a bowl and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Gradually add gelatin mixture to sour cream, stirring until well blended.
Chill until mixture begins to gel (becomes slightly thicker).
Stir in pineapple, grated carrots and chopped nuts.
Turn into mold and chill until firm, about 4 hours. Unmold onto a bed of salad greens on a chilled serving plate. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pa's biscotti
directions: Mix together in one bowl.
Roll with palms of hands long like rope, about one inch in diameter. Cut in finger shape or shape as you wish.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Ice with glaze if you wish.

title: crab dip(pizza style)
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, adding just enough sauce and seasonings so you just taste them.
Spread cream cheese mixture on plate (can be done the day before).
Spread layer of chili sauce.
Sprinkle crab on top.
Garnish with minced parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: summer pasta
directions: Mix everything except linguini in a bowl and let sit for 1/2 hour. Cool linguini and mix with mixture. Lightly toss and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion until tender; blend in seasonings. Thicken with flour. Put filling in oiled clam shells. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
