Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Layer pineapple tidbits in dish.
Mix juice, sugar and flour and pour over pineapple tidbits.
Cover with cheese and crackers. Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in shallow dish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, egg, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, flour, meal and ketchup.
Place in baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put ketchup on top and brown.

title: peanut buttered popcorn
directions: In a large roasting pan, combine popcorn and nuts. Keep warm in a 250° oven. Butter sides of a heavy 1-1/2 quart saucepan. Combine sugar, honey and corn syrup in pan. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil hard for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Immediately pour over popcorn mixture, stirring to coat well. Cool. Break into bite size pieces. Makes 3 quarts.

title: carington bean dip
directions: Blend well.
Bake at 350° until hot and heated through. Sprinkle Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese on top.
Continue baking until cheese melts.
Serve with corn chips.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soy sauce, vinegar, molasses, ginger and cornstarch in a bowl.
Cut squash into 3 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch sticks. Cut broccoli flowerets from stems.
Pare stems; cut in same size pieces as flowerets.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, lemon extract, spices and salt.
Mix well. Stir in molasses. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to mixture. Add flour to make soft dough. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: swiss onion bake
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Spread onion in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sliced eggs; sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: chicken ball
directions: Beat with mixer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Shape into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: stroganoff(leftover meat)
directions: Gently brown beef or veal in butter.
Remove meat.
Add gravy, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms.
Add meat and reheat. Serve over noodles, cooked and mixed with 2 tablespoons toasted sesame seed.
Top with sour cream and paprika.
This may be served over rice.
Delicious!

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split wings at joint and discard tips or use frozen wings that have already been prepared.
Deep fry until cooked and crispy, for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
When finished, fry.
Place wings in bowl or pan.
Pour melted butter over wings, coating well. Then pour hot sauce over wings, again making sure to coat wings well.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dip, if desired.

title: mrs. kirk's sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugars.
Beat in eggs and add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar, if desired.
Place on cookie sheet and lightly flatten.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Dough will keep for a week in the refrigerator.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Use coarse blade on grinder.
Combine all veggies in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water for 4 hours. Drain thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in drained vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack in pint jars.
Cold pack for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: kentucky fried chicken coating
directions: In double plastic food bag, combine all ingredients well. Shake mixture well.
Rinse chicken pieces in cold water, then dip in mixture.
Can deep fry or oven bake by dotting with butter and baking uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix.
Boil eight minutes, then pour on meat and bake in oven.

title: creamed carrot soup
directions: Simmer potatoes, carrots and onion in chicken stock until soft.
Puree in blender, a little at a time.
Add milk.
Melt butter in a large pot.
Blend in the flour; gradually add the pureed soup and bring to a simmer, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: kuchen(a wonderful german butter coffee cake)
directions: Mix yeast with milk.
Stir in salt and sugar.
Stir in eggs. Add oleo and flour.
Mix very well, then knead very well or use kitchen-aide mixer with dough hook.
Cover with damp cloth in a warm room until dough rises until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; rise again for 1/2 hour.
Divide dough.
Will make 2 cookie sheets or 6 pie tins.
Grease pans; put in dough and let rest for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until slightly tender.
Drain; set aside.
Brown ground meat and onion in small skillet.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Empty cake mix and dry jello into bowl. Add oil and eggs; beat 3 minutes. Add berries; beat 1 minute. Pour into two 9-inch pans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer in 9 x 9-inch square dish.
Top with tomatoes and black olives, sliced.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: cheesy-chili dip
directions: In a fondue pot, mix chili and cream cheese.
Melt together and serve on warm setting, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Fritos.

title: favorite chicken salad
directions: Put chicken in a saucepan with 3 cups of water, 1 teaspoon salt and 3 peppercorns.
Bring to a boil; lower heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Drain, bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, chestnuts, grapes and celery. Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken; toss lightly to mix.
Chill.
Spoon on lettuce and garnish with drained pineapple chunks.

title: brad's herb surprise
directions: Crush all ingredients together.
Put in shaker or Tupperware bowl with lid.
Use as a pizza topper or in spaghetti sauce or any Italian dish.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese, oleo and sour cream.
Season to taste with onion salt.
Grease a round casserole; place the potato mixture into casserole and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
May refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Bring to near room temperature and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Very smooth and creamy as just-made whipped mashed potatoes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: roquefort log
directions: Combine cheeses. Blend in next 4 ingredients. Shape into a log about 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Roll in chopped (blended) nuts mixed with parsley and 1 teaspoon paprika. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients for filling in order shown.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° until set (about 25 to 30 minutes).
If you want a browner, drier pie, bake an additional 10 minutes at 350°.

title: noodle cheese pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° or until top is golden brown.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Stir quickly and pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Put in large roaster at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
If desired, may also add peanuts.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Combine butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, then add salt, vanilla and flour. Combine buttermilk, soda and nutmeg. Mix both combinations together. Next, dump mixture into a bowl of flour, (either plain or self-rising) as if to roll out biscuits. Pinch off little balls about the size of a log-roller marble and roll them in a little flour. Place on a greased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart. Take a flat bottomed glass dipped in flour and press balls down flat until almost touching each other on the cookie sheet. (I use an old snuff glass.) Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown. Let set on cookie sheet, then store in an airtight container after they are cooled. Happy Eating!!!!!!!

title: doris' meat dish
directions: Mix together everything, but soup.
Roll into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour on soup and water.
Bake.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in butter if onions are desired.
Add additional ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine until clear and add to rice.
Combine rice mixture with salt, pepper, broccoli, soup and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Heat together the milk and water until very warm.
Add liquid to the dry mix and beat well. Stir in 3 cups of white flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into three 1-pound coffee cans which have been greased and sprinkled with corn meal.
(Pam simplifies greasing.)
Let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes.
(The loaves should be extended above the top of the cans no more than 1 inch.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from tins and cool on a rack.
Bread should sound hollow when rapped with knuckles.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add pineapple juice. Chill.
When this begins to thicken, add other ingredients.
Pour mixture into mold and chill until set.
Unmold on a plate of lettuce and serve with mayonnaise.

title: kitchen marinade
directions: Mix together and marinate meat in refrigerator over night or at least 8 hours.
Amounts are optional except for oil and juice. You can make it hotter or more mild.
If you want a red marinade add the ketchup.
Discard marinade after use.
You can baste with it, but do not serve it as a sauce unless you bring whats left to a boil.
It is best to make extra that you don't use as a marinade and use that for a sauce.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cook onion, butter, mustard and poppy seed together until onions are tender. Split each pan of rolls in half. Spread inside of rolls with butter mixture until all is used. Evenly spread ham and cheese on top of bottom layer of rolls. Add top layers of rolls. Heat in oven long enough to melt the cheese.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half.
Layer in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer crushed pineapple (drained), layer of sliced bananas, layer of vanilla pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle on nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Prepare Bisquick according to directions on package.
Roll out dough thin.
Spread sausage over dough.
Roll up like jelly roll. Wrap roll in waxed paper and chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon with fork; add remaining ingredients.
Turn into a greased baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° until firm and lightly browned, about 40 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, egg and butter all together and put in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream the cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Spread on graham crust; bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Can add 1/2 cup raisins, if desired.

title: pink fruit freeze
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, ice cream and salad dressing. Mix until well blended.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch square pan. Freeze until firm.
Place in refrigerator 15 minutes before serving. Cut into squares.
Garnish with fresh strawberries in season. Garnish with cherries and mint leaves for Christmas season.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all above ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13 inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until tested done.

title: southern style scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 1-1/2 quart round casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes.

title: oven roasted chicken fricassee
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika.
Brush chicken with melted margarine. Coat with flour mixture. Arrange chicken in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Drain off excess fat.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook celery (cut small) until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Add celery and onions.
Cook for a minute or two.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Add cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix well and chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: *beef saucy cabbage casserole
directions: In skillet, saute beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and garlic salt. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Heat mixture in crock-pot until melted and blended.
Serve as a dip over tortilla chips.

title: ham patties
directions: Combine bread crumbs, ham, eggs, milk, relish and mustard; mix well.
Shape into patties; coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in 1/2 oil and 1/2 oleo.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and salt;
beat in eggs, slowly.
Add flour, baking
soda
and baking powder; stir in nuts.
Roll in long rolls of
wax
paper
and freeze.
Slice off and bake at 325° for 8 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk and sugar to rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add chocolate squares, stirring until melted.
Beat over heat until smooth.
(If sauce has slightly curdled appearance, beat vigorously until creamy smooth.)
Remove from heat and blend in butter, vanilla and salt.
Keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: pearl's mexican corn bread
directions: Combine.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes in a glass baking dish until brown.

title: fish fillets in foil
directions: Spray 4 pieces of foil with Pam.
Melt margarine; add onion and saute until soft.
Add tomato, wine, lemon juice and chopped parsley.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Spoon over fish and wrap fish tightly.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve in foil.
Serves 4.

title: spicy peanut chicken
directions: In a wok or a large skillet over high heat, saute the onion and the garlic in half of the peanut oil until just lightly colored.
Add the red pepper, and continue to cook until the onion and garlic are golden brown.
Turn off the heat.

title: popovers(no cholesterol, 70 calories)
directions: Spray muffin tins.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat whites until fluffy, not stiff. Stir in melted margarine, milk, flour and salt. Fill pans 3/4 full.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cut slits in each and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle cheese and bacon on bottom of frozen pie shell. Combine remaining ingredients, beat slightly.
Pour batter over top.
Bake for 45 minutes in 375 degree oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Arrange berries in the pie shell, top with gelatin mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread the crescent rolls on a large cookie sheet to make the base.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Combine the next 4 ingredients and mix well.

Spread on baked rolls and top with vegetables of your choice-sliced olives, chopped green onions, small broccoli flowers, mushrooms (cut up), radish slices, green pepper or red pepper slices, Cheddar cheese (grated) or what you have.

title: inside out chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip in soup, coat with stuffing mix.
Arrange in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Serves 8.

title: brenda's brownies
directions: Melt margarine; add all other ingredients until well blended; nuts are optional.
Grease and flour pan, then pour brownie mix in.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Fix Hamburger Helper according to directions on box.
Just before you cover and simmer, add onion and mushrooms.
When this is done and ready to take up, stir in cottage cheese.
Place mixture in casserole dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place in microwave and heat long enough to melt cheese on top.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cool slightly. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly in between each egg. Spread on ungreased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan (or long cake pan).
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Press flat when cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given; pour into pie crust.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking 35 to 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: bran rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening and let stand until lukewarm, then add salt, sugar, bran and egg.
Add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add flour, using a little more than called for if necessary to make a soft dough.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise until double in size.
Work down and shape into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: jello jigglers(candy cane)
directions: Make Jell-O into Jell-O Jigglers recipe that is on the box. Pour onto cookie sheet; let set up.
Cut into candy cane shape. Using Cool Whip, make white stripes on candy cane; sprinkle with green cake decoration sprinkles.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
While hot, make holes in cake.
Pour in sweetened condensed milk.
Pour caramel topping over cake and spread.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip and candy bars!
Delicious!
Great for cookouts!

title: texas cream pie
directions: Mix flour into 1/2 cup of sugar.
Beat into egg yolks.
Slowly stir in milk.
Add salt.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly until it bubbles.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin (dissolved in cold water).
Stir well and chill.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Fold cold custard into this mixture. Pour into 2 graham crusts or 2 baked pie shells (cooled).
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream and grated chocolate.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix meal, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Put franks in batter.
Cover completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place defrosted broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix in the cream of mushroom soup, the egg, mayonnaise, grated Cheddar cheese and the onion and mix well.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Make 3 wells.
Into one pour salad oil, in another put vinegar and in the third put the vanilla.
Pour cold water over all.
Mix with a fork but do not beat.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: springtime casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup stuffing and 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese and stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and grind the pears.
Remove the seeds from oranges and grind the entire orange on medium blade of food chopper.
Do not drain pineapple.
Drain and chop cherries.
Mix all ingredients together.
Divide mixture into thirds; cook 1/3 at a time until it jells when tested on a saucer.
Put some on a saucer; turn to side and if it doesn't "run" it is thick enough.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
I do not use as much sugar.
Taste to see amount you think is best.

title: ginny's cheesecake
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes (until firm).
Cool 30 minutes or more.
Spread on top, a mixture of the last 3 ingredients.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool and place in refrigerator.

title: peggy's original m&m's cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
By hand, stir in oatmeal and M&M candies.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: butter crunch pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven.
Stir with spoon.
Press against bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan, saving about 1/2 cup for topping.
Cool before filling.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Cool thoroughly.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Divide in half and form 2 long rolls.
Roll each in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 24 hours.
Slice into 1/2-inch cookies.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift 2 cups flour with soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Dice orange slices.
Mix with 1/2 cup flour.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in coconut, nuts and oats.
Roll into balls one-inch in diameter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal haystack cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl place uncooked oatmeal and set aside. In a medium pan mix together sugar, cocoa, canned milk and butter. Boil for one minute, stirring constantly.
Add mini marshmallows and stir until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Pour over the oatmeal and mix together with a fork until it is well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let stand at room temperature overnight.

title: original kentucky hot brown
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour. Add milk, cheeses and seasonings, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened. Set aside.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: oven goulash
directions: Beef should be in chunks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in water.
Toss with 2 cups stuffing mix.
Place 1/2 in 2-quart casserole.
Mix gravy, chicken, peas and 2 cups dry stuffing.
Pour over mixture.
Top with rest of first batch of stuffing.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or so.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, flour, dates, nuts, baking powder and vanilla. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, butter and water. Bring to a boil and pour over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.
This pudding makes its own sauce.

title: halibut caddy ganty
directions: Marinate filets in wine and salt for 15 minutes. Drain and coat each filet with bread crumbs. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, red onion and dill together. Spread on top of filets like frosting. Place filets on baking dish moistened with 1 ounce white wine and 1 ounce water. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes. Garnish with dill sprigs.

title: biscuits
directions: Put desired amount of mix in bowl.
Put desired amount of cream cheese in mix (no set amount, I usually use cream cheese in a little tub and pinch some with my finger, about 25 times).
Just drop it in the mix and then stir with a tablespoon.

Then pour in 7-Up and keep stirring until you have a dough that is not too soft. You may have to add more self-rising flour to it to thicken it. Pat out on floured wax paper and cut with biscuit cutter or glass top.
Grease bottom of pan or spray with Pam.
Cook at 400° until they are as brown as you want them.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Mix flour and 1/2 cup cold water and set aside.
Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add broccoli, that is chopped, and onion.
Boil for 12 minutes.
Add seasoning and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream and butter.
Stir well until boiling.
Add flour and water paste slowly to hot mixture, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Serve with crackers or toast.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Thoroughly combine all of the ingredients, except for chips, cheese and almonds.
Place in a rectangular baking dish and top with the chips, cheese and almonds.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fettucini verole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and garlic.
Stir-fry until onions are limp.
Add noodles and cream.
Stir to mix over high heat until cream just begins to boil.
Sprinkle with cheese, then toss and mix until well coated.
Serve with more Parmesan cheese.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Mix sugar, melted butter, flour, cinnamon and sweet milk. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to boil the water, brown sugar and butter.
Pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off immediately.
Leave overnight.

title: special k bars
directions: Cook the Karo syrup and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add the peanut butter to this mixture and blend well.
Pour this over the 6 cups of cereal in a large bowl.
Mix well and put into a buttered jelly roll pan.
Melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips in the microwave.
Spread over the bars; cut into squares.

title: crab epicurean
directions: Heat butter.
Add onion and mushrooms; cook over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Add crab meat, bread crumbs, chives and seasonings.
Combine cream and egg yolk; stir into crab meat mixture.
Turn into buttered crab shells, ramekins or scallop shells.
Top with buttered crumbs and a dash of paprika.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 20 to 25 minutes, or until browned. Makes about 4 servings.
Serve with sliced tomatoes, buttered toasted garlic bread and/or Ry-Krisp.

title: steak soup
directions: Place all ingredients, except butter, flour, and salt, into crock-pot
Cover, cook on Low 8 to 12 hours (or High, 4 to 6 hours).
One hour before serving, turn on to High.	Make a paste of melted butter and flour.
Stir well until smooth.
Pour into crock-pot; stir until well blended.
Season soup with salt if desired.
Cover, cook on High until thickened.
Makes 12 servings.

title: marble cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Separate batter into 3 bowls.
Add red food coloring to one.
Leave one as is.
Add 1 teaspoon of each of the following to the other:
nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and allspice.
Pour into tube pan alternating batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 420° for 15 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles(approximately 9 pints)
directions: In large container, mix well cucumbers, onions and salt. Cover with water and ice cubes.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Set aside.
In another large pot, mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric over high heat.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: carolyn's chicken vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for potatoes and noodles; cook over medium heat in large stockpot until all ingredients are about 1/2 done.
Add cooked chicken parts (diced or chunked). Simmer until chicken is done; add potatoes and noodles and simmer until tender.
Add water for consistency desired.
Serve hot. Serves 12 to 24.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to milk, flour and eggs.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: old fashion pineapple skillet cake
directions: Melt in iron skillet brown sugar and butter. Top with pineapple slices and place a maraschino cherry in center of each slice. Beat eggs, add sugar slowly, mixing well; add pineapple juice and flour. Pour mixture over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. When done, invert on plate. Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix together milk, coconut and powdered sugar and form into balls.
Chill on waxed paper.

title: brownies from paula hardingroves, texas
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in small saucepan over low heat, cool.

title: frozen chocolate crunchy
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Mix well in a bowl.
Press mixture into a rectangular dish.
Freeze until firm.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie crust and return to freezer.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine with chocolate squares over low heat.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes until thickens.
Cool sauce and pour over ice cream. Sprinkle with pecans.
Freeze, covered, until served.

title: mrs. sipple's lemon whipples
directions: Grease a cookie sheet. Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Drop by tablespoon into the powdered sugar and roll into balls.
Place the balls on the cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Do not overbake!
If they get too brown on the bottom, it spoils the delicate lemon flavor.

title: creamy potato leek soup
directions: Place potatoes and leeks in pot with water.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, until potatoes are very tender.
Add mushrooms, garlic, dill, basil and celery seed; simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend together, in blender, Tofu Sour Cream with enough soup broth to make a thick paste.
Stir into remaining soup; add seasonings.
Do not boil after sour cream has been added.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and place on cookie sheet at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: emerson's no toll house cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and shortening.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Chill.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix dry cake mix, 1 beaten
egg
and
cup oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs.
Pat
rest of crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni patties
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add flour and blend. Add milk, salt and paprika.
Cook and stir over boiling water until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese; stir until blended.
Add macaroni, pimiento, parsley and onion.
Turn into a well-greased large flat loaf pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares and dip into crumbs, then beaten egg with water and then again in crumbs.
Fry in hot fat until a golden brown.
Garnish with parsley.

title: pumpkin bread(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin, oil and water in bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves, baking soda, nutmeg, baking powder, flour, salt and pecans.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325° or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
(Keeps well in refrigerator.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla, shredded zucchini and pineapple.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar, peanut butter, shortening and vanilla until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well.

title: squash souffle
directions: Beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into deep greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon braid
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and 1 cup margarine to 120° to 130°.
Add yolks and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in more flour to make stiff batter.
Cover bowl tightly and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Combine the last 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Turn dough out on floured board and roll into six ropes (18-inches long).
Braid three ropes together.
Seal ends firmly.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Do the last three ropes.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Cover and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Blend together sugar, Crisco, eggs, vanilla, milk, bananas and nuts.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all sugars, spices and flour.
Add pumpkin and milk last. Pour into two unbaked 10-inch pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until set and light brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat.
Take packages of cream cheese and break into small pieces so it will beat up real smooth. Add milk or cream and beat until smooth; set aside.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chips, coconut and nuts on top.
Pour over all, 1 can Eagle Brand milk.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: one-pan oven steak
directions: Cut a 3/4-inch round steak into serving size pieces.
Dredge meat into flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Pound flour into meat with a meat mallet.
In an iron Dutch oven, brown meat on both sides in hot oil.
Drain fat and add tomatoes and vegetables. Bring to a boil on top of stove with a lid.
Transfer to a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve over a bed or rice.

title: carob crunchies
directions: Melt carob chips in double boiler until smooth.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients, stirring in cereal last. Spread into
8 x 8-inch pan and chill.
Cut into chunks before serving.

title: peanut butter balls (no bake)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and dip in paste made with powdered sugar and milk.
Roll in coconut.
Lay on wax paper.

title: company pot roast
directions: Place meat in a large bowl.
Mix cider, sugar, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove meat from marinade and pat dry with paper towel. Reserve 1 cup marinade.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper and dredge meat.
Brown the meat in a Dutch oven in the oil.
Add 1 cup of the marinade and the onion.
Cover and roast 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add water to cooking liquid to make 2 cups.
Thicken with remaining 2 tablespoons flour.
Serves 8.

title: turkey noodle skillet
directions: Saute turkey meat.
When partially cooked, add onion. Continue to saute.
Then add all remaining ingredients at once with enough water to cook the noodles so your ingredients don't stick to skillet.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Line baking sheets with foil.
Wash and remove the stems from the mushrooms.
Chop and reserve 1/2 cup of the stems.
Brush the caps with the butter and place on the trays.
In a medium bowl, combine the Parmesan, mushroom stems, garlic, salt and cream cheese, blending well.
Fill the caps with the mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
These may be frozen; if so, bake 5 minutes after defrosting.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Slowly add milk.
Add Cool Whip, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate until set.
Add cherries on top.

title: breakfast yogurt bread
directions: In large bowl stir together all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, bran cereal, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Make a well in the center.
In small bowl combine egg, yogurt, milk, and oil.
Add mixture all at once to flour mixture.
Stir in fruit packages until just moistened.
Pour into a greased loaf pan (8 x 4 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove and cool or serve warm (112 calories per serving).

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat juice, sugar and softened gelatin.
Stir in lemon and cherry juice; cool.
Cream the cheese with some of the juice.
Mix in whipped cream or Cool Whip and pineapple.
Mold in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: alpine dairy scallops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/3 of the potato slices in prepared baking dish.
Top with 1/3 of the Appenzeller cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Make 2 more layers of potato slices and Appenzeller cheese.
Stir cream and onion together.
Pour evenly over layered potatoes and cheese.
Combine Parmesan cheese and paprika in a small bowl; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 2 hours until potatoes are tender and liquid is absorbed.
Garnish with snipped parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: country potatoes
directions: In a large iron skillet, melt the butter.
Add a
layer of sliced potatoes, onions and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste. Repeat layers until all vegetables are in the skillet.
Add water. Cover and cook over medium heat for 35 min.
To serve, drain off any liquid left.
Turn out onto platter and garnish with paprika, if desired.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: alcoholic punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl and add ring of ice with frozen strawberries added.

title: cato (potato pie)
directions: Mix mashed potatoes with butter, milk, eggs, salt, pepper, ham, diced cheese and parsley.
Butter a medium roasting pan and pour mixture in.
Top with grated cheese and parsley.
Bake about 1/2 hour or until lightly brown on top.

title: baked macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions; drain and reserve for later use.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples, add sugar and spices to apples.
While they are hot, roll biscuits out flat and put in 1 tablespoon of apples. Fold over and press side down.
Fry in hot shortening on one side and turn over; do the other side until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple, sugar and orange juice.
Let sit in refrigerator for several hours.
Add to ingredients and let sit.

title: quick meal
directions: Brown hamburger; salt as desired.
Add beans, soup and tomatoes.
Simmer together while hot through and through.
Serve with crackers or spoon on thin corn bread and serve.

title: peach cobbler 1
directions: Mix flour, pudding, egg, butter and milk together.
Spread in a greased glass dish.
Add peaches.
In another bowl, mix sugar, cream cheese and 3 tablespoons of peach juice.
Spread on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix seasonings with melted margarine.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in shallow pan and bake slowly at 200° or 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour, sugar and grated mild cheese.
Layer all ingredients in order.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar
and
shortening;
add beaten eggs and sour milk. Add salt
and
soda.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough. Roll out
dough
and
cut
with
large round or shaped cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a covered skillet.
Put lid on skillet and bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Do not open during cooking.
I use a cast-iron chicken frying skillet with lid.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put chops in bottom of baking dish.
Place rice over them. Slice onion and green peppers over rice.
Pour hot water and tomatoes over this and add salt and pepper.
Cover and bake 1 hour until rice is cooked and chops are tender.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix cornflakes with melted margarine, brown sugar and pecans. Top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Place meatballs into casserole dish; pour blended sauce over meatballs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: Tear up spinach.
Add onions, carrots, radishes and red cabbage.
Place oranges on top, then sprinkle on toasted almonds.

title: pineapple-strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add lemon juice; chill until set.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add cottage cheese, whipped cream, pineapple and strawberries.
Pour into a mold and chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant italiano(microwave)
directions: Pare eggplant and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Spread 2 tablespoons tomato sauce in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Layer half of eggplant, 1 can tomato sauce, half of the oregano, and half of the sharp cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover.
Microwave on Medium-high 19 to 23 minutes. Add Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until cheese has melted.

title: sponge bar cake
directions: Make strawberry Jell-O with 1 1/4 cups hot water; add frozen strawberries.
Hot Jell-O will melt berries.
Whip one box whipping cream and fold into Jell-O and berry mixture.
Let stand while you break up sponge cake in chunks in cake pan, then pour strawberries evenly over cake pieces.
Refrigerate; let set and serve.

title: baked potatoes with sesame or caraway and salt
directions: Wash potatoes and cut them the long way so that you end up with the biggest surface cut open.
Mix sesame or caraway and salt in a deep dish and dip the open surface into it until it is well covered.
Transfer the potatoes onto a cookie sheet with the covered side right on the sheet.
Apply a fair amount of olive oil with a brush on the potato skin.
Bake in the oven at 450° for 30 minutes or a little more until done (it depends on the size of the potatoes).

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add flavoring and eggs.
Sift together flour, spices, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately to first mixture with pumpkin.
Add nuts last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack and ice with lemon or orange flavoring if desired.

title: decorator cake icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric mixer bowl.
Blend at low speed, then beat at high speed until smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl often.

title: hot canapes
directions: Combine and spread on bread squares or party rye bread.
Bread can also be cut in rounds.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add milk to all ingredients (don't make batter too thin).
Drop by teaspoons and fry in lots of Crisco.

title: garden soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a large pan until beef is brown.
Drain.
Add sauce mix, water, seasonings and tomatoes. Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add macaroni and vegetables. Cover and cook until macaroni is tender, 15 minutes longer

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes; let stand in cold water while peeling rest. Grate potatoes using fine grating side.
Put potatoes in kitchen towel and wring out all surplus water.
Add egg yolks, baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiff beaten egg whites.
Use large spoon to pour onto hot greased griddle (should have about 1/8 inch oil in pan).
Cook until light golden brown on both sides.
Serve immediately; top with sour cream or applesauce. Serves 4.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Combine pepper, garlic, 1 teaspoon oregano, vinegar and 1 teaspoon oil.
Coat cutlets with mixture.
Dip cutlets in beaten egg whites.
Dip in bread crumbs in a second bowl and chill for 20 minutes.
Heat remaining oil in skillet and saute cutlets on both sides over moderate heat for 10 minutes in the frying pan with oil left in pan.
Add 1/2 teaspoon oregano and tomatoes and stir. Pour tomato onion sauce over cutlets.
Top with Mozzarella slices and grated Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shortbreads
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When golden, remove from cookie sheet.
Roll in powdered sugar and allow to cool.
Yields an average of 4 dozen, quarter-size balled cookies.

title: reese's bars
directions: Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine with peanut butter.
Stir in cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Mixture will be very thick. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and press smooth.
Melt chocolate chips and 1 stick margarine; pour over.
Refrigerate.

title: mile high pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Alternate adding sugar and strawberries and beat about 15 minutes.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and fold in whipped cream.
Place in three pie shells.
Place in freezer.
Keep frozen until ready to use.

title: mock apricot preserves
directions: Put zucchini in heavy pan over low heat.
Add no water.
Bring to a boil on low heat and boil 6 minutes.
Stir and watch carefully.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Return to stove and boil additional 6 minutes.
Stir in jello and Sure-Jell.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: milanese rice
directions: Cook rice per package directions for 4 cups.
Add butter to rice and 2 eggs, salt and grated cheese; stir well.
In baking pan, rub with soft butter.
Put a layer of tomato sauce, then rice.
Continue until all rice is in pan.
Spread tomato sauce on top, then some grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is slightly browned.

title: baked yams
directions: Cook yams; mash and add a dash of salt.
Spread in layers in casserole: mashed yams, marshmallows, chopped nuts, dot of butter and a small amount of brown sugar.
Cover top sparingly with brown sugar; place walnut halves on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: no-crust coconut pie *
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and flour.
With mixer set at low setting, blend in eggs, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie crust and cool.
Slice strawberries.
Put in pie crust.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, jello and Seven-Up until thick to make a filling; cool.
Pour over strawberries; top with Cool Whip and serve to mothers.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain well, peel and cube.
Add celery, onions and sweet pickles.
Combine salad dressing, sugar, celery seed, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Add mixture to potatoes and toss lightly to coat potatoes.
Carefully add chopped eggs. Cover and chill.
Serves 8.

title: hot cheese roll
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Into a large bowl, blend by hand the cheeses, garlic and pecans.
Form into long rolls.
On wax paper, sprinkle the crushed peppers and roll the cheese rolls in the peppers.
Enclose in the wrap, then fold and freeze.
(The chili peppers can be put into a blender and pulverized; they blend into the cheese better.)

title: brunch pie
directions: Coat 9-inch pie plate with margarine.
Mix hash and 1 beaten egg.
Press into plate to form the crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Saute onions in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Layer cheese, sauteed onions and Veg-All on crust.
Beat together remaining eggs, evaporated milk and flour.
Pour over mixture in crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until filling is set.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wedding cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and spices together 3 times.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, fruit, nuts, honey, molasses and cider.
Add flour in small amounts, mixing well after each addition.
Turn into cake pans which are greased, lined with heavy paper and greased again.
Bake in oven at 250°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Pour over fresh spinach with mandarin oranges and toasted slivered almonds.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour 1/2 melted butter into potato mixture.
Pour other half butter over Ritz crackers.
Put mixture into greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with crushed cracker mixture.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple tapioca
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer until apples are tender, about 12 minutes.
Serve warm with a sprinkle of nutmeg and a scoop of ice cream.
Also delicious served cold. Yield: 8 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions until soft.
Put into large pot of water.
Add soup powder, tamari sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Serve with toasted bread in a bowl and melted Mozzarella on top of soup.

title: penne with zucchini and sage butter
directions: Heat butter, olive oil and sage leaves in a large skillet over medium heat until browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mash potatoes; add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Cream well.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to lukewarm milk, then add to potato mixture.
Add sifted flour to make a stiff dough.
Toss on board (floured board) and knead well.
Put into large bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead slightly. Place in casserole and rub with butter.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator until ready to bake.
About one hour before baking time, pinch off dough; shape into rolls as desired.
Cover and let rise until light.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: iron skillet corn
directions: In iron skillet, brown sausage quickly.
Saute onion and pepper.
Add corn.
Stir well.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni, celery, green pepper and onion. Toss to coat well. Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: reese's bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips over boiling water. Mix together the melted butter, graham crackers, powdered sugar and peanut butter. Put all but chocolate into 9 x 13 pan and pat down. Spread
melted chocolate chips evenly over all. Chill and cut into squares.

title: almond bark pecan fudge
directions: Melt almond bark in a double boiler.
Add 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Then add marshmallows, pecans, salt and almond extract.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and cool.

title: pear pickles
directions: Heat together sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, ginger, pickling spices and water.
Add pears to the syrup along with 2 slices of lemon.
Cook pears until tender when pierced with a toothpick. Remove from heat and let stand overnight.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt 1 stick of butter, then add peaches. Pour mixture of flour, sugar and milk into pan.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.
Batter will cook up and over peaches.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Add sugar, salt and Crisco to boiling water (1 1/2 cups). Cool 1/2 cup water until lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to yeast mixture.
Stir when dissolved.
Add to well beaten eggs, then mix the two parts together.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Beat well.
Let rise 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Punch down and let rise again.
Shape rolls.
Place in baking pan. Let rise.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: mexican casserole(makes 8 to 12 servings)
directions: Boil noodles as per the instructions on the package.
Brown ground beef.
(I usually sprinkle a little seasoning salt on the ground beef.)
Drain all the fat off the ground beef.
Mix the corn (drained), noodles, ground beef, Ro-Tel, cream of celery and mushroom soups in a big mixing bowl.
Melt the Cheez Whiz in the microwave; pour into the mixture.
Mix all these ingredients. Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Place cheese slices on the top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes (times may vary).

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix all ingredients as for pie crust.
Place 1/2 of mixture into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press firmly.
Cover with pie filling.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Press lightly. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When done, cool and cut into squares.

title: melting moments cookies
directions: Sift flour and cornstarch. Cream butter and sugar. Combine the two mixtures. Drop onto cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Frost with Lemon Frosting while still slightly warm. Yield about 4 dozen cookies.

title: marshmallow square
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Press into 8 x 8-inch lightly greased pan.
Refrigerate.
This can be doubled for 9
x 13-inch pan.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and continue beating. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and dates.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Do not overbake.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Add cherry juice; mix until smooth.
Fold in whipped Cool Whip.
Add pecans.
Chill 30 minutes.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.
Top with pie filling.
Lightly cover with waxed paper.
Refrigerate before serving.
Can be made up 1 day in advance.

title: ceviche
directions: Flake the crabmeat in a large mixing bowl and douse with juice of one (1) lime.
Add avocados, onions and peppers.
Stir gently.
Season with ground pepper and juice from the second lime. Cover and refrigerate.
Serve from your prettiest bowl surrounded by pita bread, triangles, party crackers, endive spears and remaining two (2) limes sliced.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: cube steaks with onion relish
directions: Cut onions into thin wedges.
Heat butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions; saute until browned, 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Stir in vinegar, salt and pepper. Remove relish to serving bowl.
Wipe skillet clean with paper toweling.
Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add steaks in single layer; cook 1 minute each side or until cooked through. Serve with relish.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Make cream sauce (make a little more than called for).
Add ham and cheese; then add noodles.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deviled crab and shrimp
directions: Mix everything, except crumbs and cheese together.
Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Sprinkle meat squares with salt, pepper and flour.
Brown with onions in the oil.
Add water to cover; simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Add the vegetables; cook until tender.
Season with salt and pepper and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: texas gold bar
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with mixer.
Spread in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour on top of first layer.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spicy turkey spaghetti
directions: Heat the milk, soup and tomatoes over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until boiling.
Add turkey, along with salt and pepper to taste.
Continue heating for several minutes on low heat.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour sauce over cooked noodles.
Top with Parmesan cheese or bread crumbs; bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add bananas and flour and soda sifted together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Cream together:
margarine, sugars and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well so oil won't separate.
Add flour mixed with salt, soda and cream of tartar and mix well.
Stir in cereals, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten slightly.
Bake on lower shelf at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes. Move pan to shelf at middle of oven and finish baking until lightly browned another 5 minutes or so.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: large vegetable casserole
directions: Layer or mix together and bake at 400° until bubbly.
Add onion rings on top last 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together with electric mixer, then blend all other ingredients in.

title: muenster chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in beaten egg yolks overnight if possible. Dredge chicken in bread crumbs and brown in butter in hot skillet. Place browned chicken in baking dish and pour chicken broth over all.
Top with shredded Muenster cheese.
Bake at 350° for at least 30 minutes or until cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: steamed crabs - maryland style
directions: Pour water and vinegar in 10 gallon pot with platform (wood or stainless steel) for bottom of pot, making sure liquid is not over platform.
Place a layer of crabs, using tongs, on platform. Sprinkle generously with seafood seasoning and salt.
Continue to layer crabs until all are in pot.
Place a very damp cloth over pot.
Cover with lid.
Place pot on low to medium heat and steam 45 minutes to 1 hour or until crabs are an orange-red color. Serve with ice cold beer.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in bowl (microwaving is easiest).
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla and cream together.
Add flour to mixture a little at a time and stir in until moist. Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 10-12 minutes or until edges start to brown.
If desired add more flour to use cookie cutters or cookie press.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix ingredients well; chill.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad(one large bowl)
directions: *Use floweret part.
Cut some, if desired.
Cut/slice thin the top stem that is tender.

title: strawberry bread and butter
directions: Combine dry ingredients; beat eggs and add strawberries and oil.
Fold into dry ingredients.
Spray 4 small loaf pans with Pam.
Divide dough equally and smooth hollow into top.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Bread may be frozen.

title: chicken tenders
directions: Dip the chicken strips into the flour until covered, then transfer them into the egg mixture.
Again making sure the strips are covered, transfer them into the bread crumbs.
Continue these steps until all chicken strips are done.
Fry the chicken until golden brown.
Serves 4 people.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla in large bowl. Make into small balls.
Insert toothpicks in top of balls and place on cookie sheet.
Chill for 2 hours.
Mix chocolate and wax and melt together slowly.
Dip chilled peanut butter balls in melted chocolate, leaving tiny spot at the top of each ball uncovered with chocolate mixture to give "buckeye" effect.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; place in greased casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients (except dressing and margarine) together and pour over broccoli.
Cover with dressing then dribble margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover for first half of baking time, then uncover for remaining time to brown.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chicken, tomatoes and soups.
Cook until mixture bubbles. Grease long casserole dish.
Layer chips and chicken mixture, ending with chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer Tater Tots, meat, cheese and onion in a 9 x 15-inch pan. Mix eggs, seasonings and milk.
Pour over ingredients in pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: jackie's fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage the sugar, milk, butter and salt. Stir until melted chocolate chips.
Beat quickly; turn off heat. Stir in marshmallow, nuts and vanilla.
Beat again; pour in well greased pan.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil brown sugar, nuts and oleo together for 2 minutes. Line cookie
sheet
with
graham
crackers.
Cover with boiled ingredients and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil noodles; cool with cool water and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with good Italian dressing.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut all the vegetables into small pieces.
Mix salt, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Mix all the dressing with the vegetables at least 24 hours in advance of serving.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: barbecued venison roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper.
Melt fat in a heavy pan; add roast and brown slowly on all sides.
Add garlic and celery. Add water to vinegar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce to make 1 cup liquid.
Pour over roast.
Cover and bake slowly for 3 hours or until tender.
Remove roast; add flour and water paste to pan liquid to make delicious gravy.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add flour which has been sifted with soda and cream of tartar.
Add nuts and shape into rolls; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Slice thin and bake in moderate oven, 350° until brown.
Dough keeps well; it can be frozen and used several days later.
(This was one of our girl's favorite cookies.)

title: pie shells
directions: Mix well the flour, shortening and salt.
Beat egg, vinegar and water together; add to flour and beat until smooth.
Roll between wax paper.
This makes enough for 2 pies or 4 custards.

title: caramel sheet cake
directions: Mix yellow cake as directed.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet pan.
Let cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix the gelatin with 1 pint boiling water in a large bowl. Let sit in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Then beat in the condensed milk and mayonnaise.
Stir in crushed pineapple, including juice, and nuts.
Leave in the bowl or pour into individual molds and let stand in the refrigerator until jelled. Serves 8.

title: sesame rainbow trout
directions: Preheat gas grill to medium heat.
Wash and dry fish.
Combine ingredients and brush fish with mixture.
Cook fish on greased grill only until very light brown (5 to 8 minutes).
Brush fish with butter mixture and turn carefully.
Cook fish until flesh flakes when tested with a fork.

title: great party chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Pour mixture over chicken wings in a large bowl or casserole.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Place on a rack over shallow pan, basting often.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° or until golden brown.
(These do not have to be turned.)

title: old-fashioned butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix soft butter, sugar, flour, salt and vanilla well.
Spread on large cookie sheet very thin with fingers.
Beat egg and spread over batter in pan.
Drain off excess egg.
Cover
with finely chopped nuts, firming them onto the dough.
Cook in oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares as soon as taken from oven.

title: great seasonal grape salad
directions: Melt butter; add flour and slowly stir in milk.
Add 12 marshmallows, one at a time, until melted and then remaining 12 marshmallows.
Then remove from heat.
Add pineapple and grapes, mix well and refrigerate.
Serve in mounds on lettuce.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Divide sugar into 3 equal parts.
Add 5 egg yolks and cream good.
Add coffee and flavoring in buttermilk. Sift flour and measure.
Second time, add cocoa, soda and salt. Sift again.
Start with flour and add milk, but end with flour. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° until done. Makes 3 layers.

title: the best applesauce
directions: Cube apples.
Place in 3-quart saucepan with juice or cider. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and the spice of your liking. Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Mash in the pot or cool and puree
in processor.
Refrigerate up to two weeks.

title: fudgie snacking cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. (Raisins or nuts may be added if desired.)

title: marshmallow clouds
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In a large bowl, combine sugars.
Using electric mixer, add butter, eggs and vanilla; beat at medium speed.
Add flour mixture and chocolate chips; blend at low speed.

title: garlic dip
directions: With fork, mix cream cheese and milk in small bowl until it has the texture of peanut butter.
Press garlic and add to cream cheese mixture.
Salt to taste and mix thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape (juicy) mixture into loaf (bread pans or shallow baking dish).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Stir all ingredients together. Spoon into 12 x 17-inch pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: japanese snow pea soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until just heated through.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: In saucepan or small skillet, bring to boil the potatoes and enough salted water to cover.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain well.
In large skillet, heat oil; add potatoes. Cook, stirring and shaking skillet, 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are golden.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cook briefly. Add green pepper and cook, stirring gently as necessary, about 3 minutes.
Add butter; cook about 2 minutes.
Gently stir in pimiento; cook until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: garden de lite bars(serves 12)
directions: Thin mayonnaise with a little milk, if desired.
Lay crescent roll flat on cookie sheet.
Punch holes with fork.
Bake as instructed on can and allow to cool.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate, boiling water and shortening in the top of a double boiler until chocolate is melted and mixture looks glossy when beaten slightly.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix and make 2 long rolls.
Chill or freeze overnight.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cucumber-cream cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add lemon juice, horseradish, salt and hot sauce. Stir in onion and cucumber.
Put in a covered container. Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook Tennessee Pride Country sausage in a skillet until it loses its pink color, stir to break up sausage and drain off fat. Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash for 5 minutes in small amount of water.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spinach squares(no crust quiche)
directions: Saute onion; cool.
Beat eggs and add cottage cheese.
Add crumbled Feta cheese.
Defrost and drain spinach and add to mixture.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake in 400° to 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: franks oriental-style
directions: Mix water, soy sauce, honey, sugar, cornstarch, garlic powder and ginger.
Cook hot dogs in oil, just until edges begin to curl. Stir in soy sauce mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and hot dogs are evenly coated, adding the green onions.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Melt butter and pour over potatoes.
Add onion.
Toss together.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour, cream, salt, and pepper.
Mix all together and put into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Cover with cheese.
Bake about 45 minutes or until golden brown at 350 degrees. Better if mixed the night before.

title: steak soup
directions: In a large pot, brown the beef; drain fat. To meat in pot, add undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, mixed vegetables and onion soup. Mix water, pepper, oregano and sugar.
Add to soups. Stir to mix. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer 1 hour.

title: round steak and rich gravy
directions: Make sure meat has been tenderized; sprinkle meat with a little garlic powder, pepper and salt.
Layer meat; cover with golden mushroom soup and then mushrooms and water in can.
Keep layering until all of soup and mushrooms are gone.
Use crock-pot on high until done, usually all day.
Bigger quantities take much longer.
Cook overnight and next morning, if needed.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and pull apart cauliflower.
Mix together the sugar and Miracle Whip.
Spread over top of vegetables.
Top with cheese and cover with plastic wrap.
Let it sit in the refrigerator overnight.
Stir together before serving.

title: black beans(serve with rice and picadillo)
directions: Sort black beans for pebbles!
Soak overnight and simmer 4 to 6 hours or cook
in pressure cooker 45 to 50 minutes (chill pot when done).
Serve with sliced onion on top.
Serve with rice and picadillo.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix.
Add egg yolks, mix.
Add flour and soda to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° in three greased and floured 8-inch cake tins.
Cool and frost.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Let cream cheese set out to get soft before mixing.
Combine French onion dip, cream cheese and chili powder in mixing bowl. Mix well.
Spread evenly on flat round plate (pizza pan).
Spread taco sauce evenly on top of mix.
Layer cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and olives evenly.
Nacho chips or your favorite chip may be used to dip.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening until creamy.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamy mixture in small amounts.
Add milk and vanilla flavorings.
Place in Bundt pan or tube pan at 350° and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour; beat well until smooth.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in an angel food cake pan.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove and set aside.
Add chives, dill weed, salt and pepper. Stir in chicken broth.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Keep warm.
In a small bowl, combine flour and sour cream.
Stir sour cream mixture into skillet.
Cook until heated through; do not boil.
Serve over chicken.

title: broccoli and ham salad
directions: Combine broccoli, ham and cheese in a large bowl.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix ingredients, except vanilla, into microwavable bowl.
Cook in microwave for 3 minutes, stirring at 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat out lumps and pour into 8-inch glass dish.
(Can substitute 4 tablespoons peanut butter for cocoa.)

title: raspberry fudge cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan and dust with cocoa; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.

Melt 3 semi-sweet chocolate squares, unsweetened chocolate squares and butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Whisk together jam, liqueur and eggs in a large bowl; whisk in melted chocolate mixture and flour mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes; remove sides of pan and cool cake completely on wire rack.
If desired, wrap cake airtight and store at room temperature until ready to serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Peel the potatoes and onion and cut them in slices.
Put the butter in a frying pan.
Add the onion.
Fry until it is a golden brown.
Turn into the soup kettle.
Add the potatoes, rice and carrot, scraped and cut into slices.
Add the water.
Cook slowly until all the vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add melted chocolate, then add vanilla, salt and flour (nuts, if desired). Blend by hand until fairly smooth.
Batter may be slightly lumpy. Pour batter into a greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook cornmeal and water together stirring until batter becomes stiff.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oil and milk.
Gradually stir in beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Blend into cornmeal mixture.
Add onions and mix well. Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.

title: prosciutto and melon(italian hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Cut the melon into 8 wedges.
Remove the seeds from each wedge, but leave on the skin.
Make crosswise cuts 1/2-inch apart into each wedge, cutting down close to the skin.
Lay the wedges on serving plates or a serving platter.
Drape a piece of Prosciutto across the top of each wedge of melon.
Top with a lime wedge.

title: red devil cake
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add cake flour (sifted) and buttermilk.
Mix vinegar and soda, then add to batter.

title: man-o-man chili(chili is delicious any time!)
directions: In a large soup pan, brown hamburger, but don't drain.
Add tomato sauce, water, red beans, onion and green peppers and cook for 15 minutes.
Stir in chili mix.
Cook for 20 minutes.
If desired, add jalapeno pepper five minutes before chili is done, then remove before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain fat.
Set aside.
In a medium casserole dish, mix all ingredients together.
Add ground chuck. Cook, uncovered, for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs;
add
milk and melted oleo.	In another bowl add corn,
sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Combine the 2 mixtures
together	and bake in a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish at 350°
for
1 hour.	Stir every 10 minutes the first 30 minutes of cooking
time.
The
pudding
is done when a knife goes in and comes out clean.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump the apples and cherries into cake pan.
Then dump cake mix in.
Melt the butter and pour on top.
Cook in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: new potatoes with gravy
directions: Clean the potatoes with brush. Wash thoroughly.
Put in a large cooker; cover with water. Cook until tender. Add margarine. Mix flour, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over the potatoes and cook until smooth and thickened, adding more water if necessary.

title: lentil soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ham, sausage, onion and garlic in oil until onion is tender, but not brown.
Drain grease.
Stir in lentils, celery and 3 quarts of water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 2 to 3 hours or until lentils are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and hot sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes more or to desired consistency.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Process oil, vinegar, 2 tablespoons basil, green onion, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in blender or food processor until smooth.
Put pasta, bell peppers, tomato wedges, nuts and olive in large bowl.
Pour on dressing; toss and mix.
Roll cheese cubes in remaining basil to coat.
Add to salad.
Sprinkle with oregano. Toss lightly.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: bean and carrot salad
directions: Put all vegetables in a shallow dish.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salad oil and salt and pour over vegetables.
Cover dish and set in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar real good.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk and flour gradually.
Add vanilla and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cocoa brownies supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat until fluffy. Add cocoa and mix.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast brunch casserole
directions: Place croutons on bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch pan or baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Top this with sausage.

title: sauteed zucchini with onion and garlic
directions: In skillet melt butter; add zucchini and onion.
Saute until tender.
Add garlic powder to taste.

title: wiener stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Serve with saltines or any soup crackers.
Serve with pickles and catsup on side.

title: broccoli casserole #5
directions: Cook
broccoli	5
minutes (omitting salt); drain.
Cut into small
pieces
and	cover
bottom
of
buttered baking dish.
Stir together soup, cheese, mayonnaise, egg, milk and chestnuts slowly until well blended. Pour
over	broccoli.
Mix	bread
crumbs in melted butter and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quick peanut-mallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate or almond bark in a double boiler or heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir and remove from heat.
Add roasted peanuts (light salt).
When cool, but not set, add miniature marshmallows.
Stir to coat.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough oil to moisten mixture (about 1/8 cup).
Stuff caps with mixture and place on well oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: 7-grain bread
directions: Boil water, add milk and heat to scalding.
Add salt, canola oil and molasses, then add 1/2 cup each of 7 different grains and cool mixture to lukewarm, then add whole wheat flour, white flour and yeast.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour on heavily floured board and knead, adding flour as needed.
Let rise until double in bulk and bake in 350° oven until done.
Very good and healthy too!

title: low calorie cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese.
Drain pineapple and add together with cream cheese, then add chopped green pepper, onion, salt and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Mix altogether, forming a ball and chill for 15 minutes.
Cover with remaining nuts.

title: congo squares
directions: Place margarine and sugar in saucepan and melt on medium heat. Place in bowl, add eggs and beat.
Add Bisquick.
Mix in 2 portions.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, leaving out half of the nuts. Shape into 2 balls.
Roll each ball in the rest of the nuts. Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: swiss apple squares
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased square (8 x 8-inch) pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini, mushroom and tomato casserole
directions: In a 2 quart buttered casserole, alternate layers of zucchini, onion, tomatoes and mushrooms with combined salt, basil and Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter and bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks with milk and sugar.
Cook until slightly thick. Pour over layered strawberries and wafers.
Beat egg whites; put on top and brown.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix pie filling and milk together, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: duck gumbo over wild rice
directions: Skin a medium to small size duck; boil in water with 1 medium size onion and several stalks of celery.
