After several hours, the duck should come off the bones by pulling it carefully.
Set aside to cool in the refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 x 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: fried dough
directions: Beat eggs; add soda to sour milk.
Put baking powder, nutmeg and salt into flour.
Mix all ingredients, including Crisco.
The dough should be soft, but not sticky, so add flour accordingly. Flatten dough on floured surface to about 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Cut into small pieces about 2-inches square.
Drop into hot melted Crisco.
They'll puff up and turn light brown when done.
Drain on paper towels and serve with syrup, spaghetti sauce, confectioners sugar or cinnamon.

title: cashew "jack" cheese
directions: Whiz
all
ingredients,
except
oil, until smooth.
If using oil, slowly add until thick (while blending).
Pour into bowl
and refrigerate.
Use as cheese sauce over vegetables or beans.

title: iced mocha
directions: Combine milk, syrup and coffee; mix well.
Pour over crushed ice in glasses.
Top with whipped topping and chocolate shavings, if desired.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients. Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add flour mixture.
Blend well; add nuts.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: margaritas
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator until ready to enjoy. Best if made several hours before serving.

title: skor candy bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
While hot, poke holes in cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk on top; cool.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush candy in food processor.
Top cake with candy; refrigerate.
Eat and enjoy.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate candy cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is hot, poke holes and pour milk over cake.
Let cake cool, then spoon Cool Whip over top and crumble candy bars over top.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put stewing meat in bottom of saucepan.
Add soup mix, the other 3 cans of soup and wine.
Cook slowly (250°) for 3 to 4 hours.

title: black eyes and rice
directions: Lightly brown onion.
Add peas, rice and tomatoes.
Heat and add seasonings.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Blend in flour and cheeses.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in broccoli. Place in 1-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Bread and fry cutlets.
Cook spinach.
Drain well (1 hour). Mix and heat soup and butter.
Layer spinach, chicken and soup in pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Cook until bubbly at 350°.

title: buttery bubble bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water and add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 1 cup flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface. Knead until smooth 6-8 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size. About 1 hour. Punch dough down, turn onto lightly floured surface. Shape into 1 1/2 inch a balls, dip the balls in melted oleo and arrange in a greased 9 inch fluted tube pan. Drizzle with remaining oleo. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes before inverting onto serving platter. Serve warm.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in sifter.
Mix with next 6 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: judy's stew
directions: Remove the meat and onion.
Add to all the rest of the pot.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Open bread flat on cookie sheet.
Spread sausage out in a layer.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage, starting at side of bread. Roll lengthwise.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Slice and serve.

title: creamy louisiana red beans and fluffy white rice
directions: Wash
and pick over red beans, then soak overnight or 6 to 8 hours
in
enough
water to cover.
Then drain beans and place in a
large
pot or pressure cooker.
Melt fat or drippings
in skillet.
Add
minced
onion and saute until golden brown.
Add to
red beans along with 5 cups water, seasonings and ham hock. Add salt to taste after beans have cooked for a while, tasting
to see
how
much
the ham bone has salted it before
putting in any additional salt.
Cover and cook slowly for 3
to 4 hours or until tender and creamy.
Additional water may be added as needed. If pressure cooker is used, set gauge at
15 pounds of pressure and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve on Fluffy White Rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, yogurt and curry.
Pour over other ingredients and toss well.
Great as salad or in pita pockets.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: In electric mixer, mix jello and cake mix.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Pour in oil and extract.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Glaze with powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Frost while still warm (wait about 10 minutes).

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls and brown in electric skillet on all sides.
Add 1/2-inch water; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and add to your favorite sauce; reheat and eat.

title: green bean bake
directions: Cook and drain green beans according to directions on package. Blend soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth in a 1-quart casserole.
Stir in beans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with onion.
Bake for 5 minutes longer so onions are nicely brown.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix ingredients together except nuts.
Add the nuts after mixing the other ingredients well.
I dust the nuts with a little flour.
Put into greased and floured tube pan.
(I use wax paper in the bottom of mine.)
Bake at 350° until toothpick test shows cake is done.
This cake is delicious served plain or it can be served with whipped cream and strawberry slices for garnish.
Eat and enjoy!

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 greased pie pans. Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes or longer until firm.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Heat together Coca-Cola, oleo and cocoa until oleo is melted. Set aside to cool.
Sift flour, sugar and soda into a bowl.
Add about 3 cups miniature marshmallows and stir to coat all.
Beat eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add this mixture to the Coca-Cola mixture.
Stir this into the dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan.
(I prefer a sheet cake pan or a 15 x 11-inch cake pan, but any flat cake pan may be used.
A larger pan gives a brownie texture with more icing.)
Bake in a 350° oven unti the center is barely done.
Test with a toothpick.
No definite time can be given, depends on the size of the pan used.

title: flop cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a long cake pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill cream at least 6 hours in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until partly set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
In another bowl, whip chilled cream until peaks form.
Fold into jello mixture.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Save some for top. Pour lemon mixture on top of crumbs.
Sprinkle top.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add butter and milk and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine beef, refried beans and garlic powder.
Place 4 uncooked noodles in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half of beef mixture over the noodles.
Top with 4 more noodles and remaining beef mixture.
Cover with 4 more noodles.
Combine water and salsa.
Pour over all.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Drain the chiles.
Using a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, line the dish with alternating layers of chiles, Muenster and Jack cheeses, beginning with chiles on the bottom.
Repeat until all are used. Separate eggs.
Beat yolks, adding flour, salt and milk.
Beat whites; fold in yolk mixture.
Pour over chiles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove and pour tomato sauce over top; bake 30 minutes longer.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: french apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease pie plate (9-inch).
Mix apples and spices.
Turn into plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender for 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate and sprinkle with Streusel Topping.
Bake until knife in center is clean, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well and add flavoring.
Sift flour and measure; combine with salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to first mixture.
Add coconut and mix thoroughly.
Form into rolls 2 inches in diameter.
Chill overnight.
Cut into slices.
Place on slightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake in a hot 400° oven about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix vanilla instant pudding with milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip and blend together well.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer graham crackers, half of the pudding mix, another layer of crackers and the rest of the pudding.
Add the last layer of crackers and spread chocolate icing on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: candy treats
directions: Mix all together.
Makes a pretty Christmas treat.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix together flour, salt and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix starter, warm water and oil.
Add flour mixture to starter mixture.
Mix well preferably with dough blender.
Place in greased plastic bowl and put in warm place.
Cover.
Let set overnight or all day.
Knead on floured board.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Makes 3 loaves.
Let rise again for 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Lightly butter bottom of saucepan.
Saute oysters until edges curl.
Add butter, let it melt.
Add milk mixture and egg yolks. Add salt and pepper.
Do not boil.
Serve hot with oyster crackers.

title: ham and cheese layered salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool.
Place lettuce in a layer in bottom of a large bowl. Then add macaroni.
Arrange carrots in layer over macaroni, then layer peas.
Next layer onions, then ham.
Combine mayo and dill.
Spread over the top of the salad. Cover with Saran wrap and chill several hours.
Just before serving, toss well to coat.
Garnish with eggs.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease off.
Add tomatoes and cream cheese.
Blend well.

title: aunt shirley's vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for at least one hour or until all vegetables are tender.
Serve hot with grilled cheese sandwiches for a warm winter lunch.

title: taco salad
directions: In a small skillet, brown beef with spices and salt.
Crumble meat as it cooks.
Cool.
Combine lettuce and taco chips in a large salad bowl.
Next, mound Veg-All in center.
Surround with beef, tomato, cheese and onions.
Add dressing and toss at table just before serving.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: In large saucepan, bring margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk to boil.
Cook for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight for full flavor.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° until done.

title: so easy chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Reserve 1/3 cup frosting.
In large bowl, combine remaining frosting, peanut butter and egg; blend well.
By hand, stir in flour.
Using about 1 tablespoon of dough per ball, shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
With the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar, flatten each ball to 2-inches in diameter.
Bake until set, about 4 to 7 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Lightly frost with reserved 1/3 cup frosting.

title: baked beans
directions: Boil beans as instructed on package, using only salt and pepper to season. Pour cooked beans into baking dish. Slice onion and layer over beans. Place bacon slices over the onion rings. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: In food processor, process ingredients until a smooth spread. Chill until ready to use.
Spread can be chilled for several hours to firm and shaped into a ball or log and rolled in chopped parsley or walnuts.

title: swiss steak
directions: Coat beef with flour, salt and pepper. Heat oil in a large skillet. Brown beef in a skillet, then add tomatoes, celery and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer for about 1 hour. Serve with hot rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Chop green onions and mix with cream cheese. Chop dried beef in food processor. Add half of the dried beef to the cream cheese mixture. Roll into ball and roll ball in remainder of beef.
Refrigerate until firm. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: pastry puffs
directions: Put in a saucepan water and butter.
Heat until butter melts. Add flour and stir until dough forms a ball in the center of pan. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1 egg; beat until well blended.
Add another egg; beat as before.
The mixture should be very stiff.
If not, let stand 10 minutes before shaping.
Drop with a teaspoon.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Remove from pan and allow to cool.
Split and fill with chicken salad or any spread.

title: salmon supreme
directions: Place salmon in greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon sour cream over salmon.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven or until salmon flakes easily.

title: puffed potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and beat until fluffy in a large bowl.
Season if necessary.
Spoon into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle potato sticks on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: beignets
directions: Heat milk until almost boiling, stirring so as not to scorch. Place shortening and sugar in a large bowl; pour milk over and stir until smooth and melted.
Cool to lukewarm, then add yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Sift dry flour and salt into another bowl.
Stir about half of this mixture into milk mixture gradually and then add egg.
Beat in remaining flour.
Set aside and let rise until double.
Knead.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Cover and let rise again, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Drop squares into hot oil (385°), turning once when golden brown on bottom side. Drain on paper towels and dust with powdered sugar.
Serve warm. Makes 2 dozen.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook a hen and cut into small bits.
Cook the bell pepper, celery and onions in some of the chicken broth until tender.
Add the noodles. When noodles are cooked, add the remaining ingredients. This will serve 20 people.

title: country crust white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead 10 to 15 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn greased side up.
(At this point, dough can be stored 3 to 4 days.)
Cover.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide in half.
Place in two greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Brush loaves with butter when done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed; pour into a 1 quart baking dish.
Place in a larger pan of water and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be mixed a day ahead and baked when needed. Serves 4 to 6.

title: copper mountain cake
directions: Mix cake by directions.
Add pecans.
Bake as directed.
Mix condensed milk and topping.
After removing cake from oven, poke holes into cake; cover with topping.
Let cool completely.
Ice with Cool Whip and candy bits.

title: layer fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add jam, cocoa and spices.
Add buttermilk and 2 cups flour alternately. Add soda, salt and vanilla. Dredge fruit and nuts in 1 cup flour. Add fruit and nuts, then add wine or whiskey.
Cook in layers (5) at 375° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
(Can be cooked in 3 loaf pans at 325° until done.)

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash the avocados, discarding the pits.
Add the lemon juice, onion and salt.
Place in serving bowl, spreading the mayonnaise on top, sealing to edges of the bowl.
Chill.
At serving time, stir in mayonnaise and cooked bacon which has been crumbled or bacon bits.
Serve with corn chips.

title: helen's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese together.
Adding eggs and baking powder and flavorings.
Add flour last, and do not mix too much after adding flour.
Pour in large tube pan (greased and floured).
A Bundt pan will NOT hold this cake.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours on 325.
You can used the baking powder or not.
To make a crunchy top; put the cake in a cold oven.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Advance Preparation:
Combine rice, broth, soup, 1/4 cup water, pimiento and onions.
Turn into 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Place chicken atop; season with salt and pepper.
Cover; chill.

title: hot milk pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add flour, baking powder, salt and flavoring; beat well.
Heat milk and butter until it boils.
Add to egg mixture and beat well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven; cool 5 minutes in pan.
Turn onto cake plate and cover.
Let steam stay until cake is cooled.
This makes it very moist.
Needs no icing.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, pepper, onion and celery together.
Next, mix sugar, vinegar and cooking oil together and pour over kraut mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly the flour, nuts and butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on cooled flour mixture.
Chill.
Mix and beat until thick the pudding mix, milk and vanilla.
Pour over the chilled cake mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: grandma's washboard cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees about 10 minutes. Adding nuts, chocolate chips and raisins makes these even better!

title: crispy chicken supreme
directions: Place crushed cereal in shallow dish. Stir in paprika; set aside. In second pan, beat egg and milk slightly. Add flour, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter. Coat with crushed cereal.

Place in single layer, skin side up, in well-greased or foil lined shallow baking pan. Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Do not cover pan or turn chicken.

title: grandma hinkle's cucumbers and tomatoes
directions: Combine the first three ingredients.
Then add liquid dressing.
This may be adjusted.
Some people like less liquid.

title: bacon and chestnuts
directions: Soak chestnuts in soy sauce at least one hour (may add 1/4 cup brown sugar for sweet/sour taste).
Wrap bacon around chestnuts and secure with a toothpick.
Bake ahead of time at 350° about 30 minutes.
Drain grease and broil before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cut shortening into flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers (I like "Wheat Thins").

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt shortening and fry onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Remove.
Melt butter in skillet; add flour until it makes a paste.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add salt, pepper, chicken, sauteed vegetables, pimento, mushrooms and parsley.
Reduce heat and cook additional 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: While potato is hot, mix with sugar and shortening.
Cool. Mix all into soft dough.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Bake at 475° until brown and butter while hot.
Serve with preserves.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and not too shaky in middle.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine other ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: celebration punch
directions: The day before, mix the tangerine juice with 1 1/2 cups water. Put in freezer tray and freeze into cubes.
Mix the lemonade and orange juice concentrates with 4 1/2 cups water in a chilled punch bowl.
Put in the tangerine ice cubes and also 1 tray plain ice cubes.
Add the strawberries and chilled ginger ale.
Yields about 3 quarts, approximately 15 servings.

title: "apricot nectar"(1973)
directions: Mix together cake mix and jello; set aside.
Beat well the oil, apricot nectar and eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
With a fork, poke holes all over cake, while hot, then pour frosting mixture over cake.

title: low-fat tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Pour this over slaw.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: burnt caramel fudge
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a large pan to boil.
At the same time, put 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy skillet to caramelize. Continue shaking skillet or stir with a spoon at low temperature to mix sugar and keep from burning.
When mixture boils up to a golden brown (be sure and not let it boil up too long and lose its color), pour into first mixture that is boiling.
This will boil up for a minute, so it is necessary to use the large pan.
Cook until it makes a soft ball in cold water or 240°.
Remove from fire.
Add 1/2 stick butter and the vanilla; let set for just a minute, then beat until it holds its shape when dropped from a spoon.
Add the toasted pecans or walnuts.
Drop onto wax paper. Store in tins.

title: green salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into bowl.
Top with the crumbs.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered jar.
Refrigerate no longer than 4 weeks.
Serve on fruit or tossed salads.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole with rice, soup mix, mushrooms and liquids.
Place chicken, skin side up, over rice and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove foil last 15 minutes.

title: microwave tarragon-vegetable medley
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish, combine all veggies, except green pepper with water.
Cook, covered on High about 5 minutes or until almost tender, stirring once.
Add green pepper. Cover and cook on High 1 to 2 minutes more or until tender.
Add olives.
Stir together vinegar, sugar, oil, tarragon and salt; then stir into veggies.
Cook, covered for 30 seconds.
Serve hot or cold.
Garnish with walnuts.
If serving this cold, just marinate in vinegar dressing.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Dip chicken into egg; roll in bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
Heat oil in a medium skillet; cook chicken until lightly browned on both sides.
Pour spaghetti sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish; arrange chicken on sauce.
Top with cheeses. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: italian sausages and peppers
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, heat Italian-sausage links with water to boiling.
Cover and cook
5 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking, turning sausage frequently until water evaporates and sausage links are well browned, about 20 minutes. Remove sausage links to paper towels to drain.

title: corny clam chowder
directions: Place soups, corn and water in pan.
Heat until steaming, stirring often.
Add milk and heat to steaming again.
Do not boil.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: salsa
directions: Blend all ingredients together in food processor. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole ala inez
directions: Combine all but chicken.
Put raw chicken pieces on top of rice.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: very easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except uncooked lasagna.

Pour 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer 3 pieces uncooked lasagna over sauce, cover with 1 1/2 cup sauce, and spread 1/2 of the cheese mixture over sauce. Repeat layers of lasagna, sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagna and remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil tightly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, remove foil and bake about 10 minutes longer.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting for easier handling.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Mix all the ingredients except oil.
Do not beat eggs.
Put 1/2 cup oil in hot skillet.
Add 1/4 of mixture to hot oil.
Spoon in remainder.
Turn mixture over when edges are brown (makes like a small package).

title: easy roast beef
directions: Place roast into deep baking dish.
Add soups plus 3 cans water.
Mix and pour over roast.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: deep dish pizza casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add green pepper; mix lightly.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, onions and mushrooms.
Spoon dinner mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with beef mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; add onion.
Add and bring to a boil tomatoes, kidney beans, corn and taco seasoning.

title: mexican beans
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, brown the meat.
Drain off all grease; saute onion and pepper.
Combine all ingredients in skillet or Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Add some of the liquid from the beans if it's too dry.

title: helen brown's hot rolls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup warm water, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 package yeast.
Set aside.

title: pink cloud saladspringfield, missouri
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Drain off cherry juice and add to cream cheese.

title: glazed beef loaf(our family favorite!)
directions: Combine egg, bread, milk, salt and pepper in large bowl and mix well.
Add chuck, cheese, carrot and onion; mix well. Shape mixture into a loaf and place on a lightly greased rack in a broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the two packages of frozen broccoli in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid.
Arrange the broccoli in a casserole dish.
Mix the can of cream of mushroom soup, cream, reserved liquid, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour this mixture over the broccoli.
Sprinkle the grated Cheddar cheese over the top of the broccoli/soup mixture.
In a pan, melt the butter or margarine.
Stir in the bread crumbs and mix until all the bread crumbs are coated with the butter. Sprinkle over the cheese topped broccoli mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: rotini casserole
directions: Saute 1/2 stick of butter and onion in a pan.
Mix all of the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place in a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chili dip
directions: Melt all ingredients together.
Serve hot with tortilla or corn chips.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix all together and let sit at least 2 hours or overnight. Excellent as a dip, sauce or to put on fish.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken in
a single layer in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt
and pepper.
Press excess liquid from sauerkraut and spoon over chicken.
Arrange corned beef and cheese slices over
sauerkraut.
Pour dressing evenly over
the
top.
Cover pan with
aluminum
foil.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is
tender.	Makes
4 servings.

title: too easy to believe cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt
and baking soda. Place in an ungreased 8 inch square pan.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
In 1 hole put the vanilla, in the second hole, the vinegar, and in the third hole the melted butter.
Pour 1 c. water over all and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Invert pan on wire rack and let stand until cake drops from pan, about 10 minutes.
Frost if desired.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together by folding.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold into milk mixture.
Add vanilla and crushed pineapple.
Fold this in and pour into graham pie shell.
Chill or freeze.

title: pennies from heaven cheese wafers
directions: Cream together margarine and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Form into marbles and place on baking sheet.
Press flat.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas skillet
directions: Mix all together in skillet. Let simmer 30 minutes; stirring occasionally.
Good with cornbread sticks.

title: donna's easy apple dip
directions: Beat together with electric mixer; add additional cream until desired consistency.
Keeps well in refrigerator 1 week or more. Serve with sliced raw apples.

title: citrus raisin strata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Tear bread into bite-size pieces. Place in a greased 2-quart square baking dish.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika chicken.
Brown in 4 tablespoons butter and put in casserole.
Saute mushrooms in remaining butter for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over them and stir in bouillon and sherry.
Arrange artichokes between chicken pieces.
Add olives. Pour mushroom sherry sauce over and bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cover tightly while baking.

title: maple walnut bars
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and blend.
Add melted butter, flour, flavoring, walnuts and raisins; blend until mixed.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch square pan and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into squares with sharp knife.
Yields 16 squares.
Yum!

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
In a long cake pan, put 2 cups graham cracker crumbs, 1 teaspoon of sugar, 2 sticks butter or margarine and pack into pan.

title: aztec salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except avocados.
Chill and serve in an avocado half on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice and 1/2 can of French Fried Onions.
Add Italian seasoning and pour into a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Pour bouillon over rice mixture.
Arrange chicken on top and pour salad dressing over chicken.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
After 30 minutes, place vegetables around chicken and bake uncovered for 20-25 minutes or until cooked.
Top chicken with remaining onions and bake 1-3 minutes longer or until onions are golden.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli flowers and small stem pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Spread chicken on top.
Combine soups, stock, egg, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder (if desired) in bowl and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Melt margarine and add dressing; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May add fresh or canned mushrooms, if desired.

title: gooey chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
"Very moist and good."

title: ice cream delite
directions: Combine first three ingredients, mix well and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: tomato beef pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes all ingredients except kidney beans.
Add kidney beans.
Put in baking dish and cover with cornbread.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Place brown sugar in pan and dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Lay peach slices on top. In mixing bowl, mix 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup butter, baking powder, salt, egg and milk until well blended. Sprinkle mixture over peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with cream if desired.

title: mom's party chicken
directions: Remove skin and excess fat from chicken.
Place chicken in an ovenproof baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper. Top each breast with a slice of cheese.
Cover with mushrooms. Mix wine with soup and pour over chicken breasts, cheese and mushrooms.
Lightly crumble stuffing mix over top.
Dribble with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add 1 cup sugar and let set for 30 minutes. Mix jello with 3 cups liquid (begin with 1 cup hot water).
Melt sugar and add 2 cans cold water with pineapple juice as part of the cold water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate.

title: farmer and fisherman chowder(tuna, salmon or flounder)
directions: Note:
One (8 ounce) can sliced green beans with liquid may be used in place of zucchini, if preferred.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frying pan.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix all together and
beat
for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch
cake
pan.
Sprinkle
1/2 cup brown sugar over the cake and bake in
a
oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except
1 cup nuts.
Make into a ball and roll in rest of nuts.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: swiss 'n' chicken casserole
directions: Mix all but nuts together. Spread in a 2-quart greased dish. Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut snacks
directions: Bring syrup and brown sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter. Pour mixture over cereal and peanuts in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: lemon-poppy seed cake
directions: Mix everything except poppy seed.
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan (or spray with Pam).
Add poppy seed to remaining 1/3 batter.
Spread on top, covering the first layer. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan (can be frozen).

title: easy lime pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell or 9-inch chocolate crumb crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Prepare oven at 350°. Cook the spinach according to package directions and drain. Mix spinach with cheese and 1/2 of the butter, then salt and pepper to taste. Stir to mix well. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Melt the remaining butter. Toss with the bread crumbs and sage; sprinkle the mixture over spinach. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly hot and lightly brown.

title: grapefruit and avocado salad* * * * *
directions: If you believe this entree came from the Southwest, you would be right.
Actually, a neighbor in Clovis, New Mexico gave it to me and I didn't use it until years later.
I was afraid of hot things and chilies, to me, at that time, were hot.
I've learned quite a bit through the years.

title: veggie chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cook in slow cooker on low for 6-8 hours or high 3-4 hours.
Also can be cooked in oven in heavy covered pot at 350 for 1-2 hours.
Serve with sour cream if people need to put the fire out.

title: mrs. field's cookie recipe
directions: *Option:
Put small amounts in blender until it turns to powder.

title: seafood stew
directions: Bring vinegar to a boil in a 6 to 8-quart heavy pot. Add onions. Turn heat to low and cover pot partially.
Cook 15 minutes until onions are soft.

title: maple cream spread
directions: Boil all together, all except egg whites.
Boil up to 240°, then cool slightly.
Slowly pour into stiffly beaten egg whites. Keep stirring every once in a while until cold. If too stiff, add a little water.
This can be used instead of Church Peanut Butter.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix the cranberry sauce, French dressing and onion soup together; pour over chicken breasts in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Chop parsley in food processor; put in salad bowl (chop fine). Chop onion and add to parsley.
Add diced tomatoes.
Wash bulgur; drain water and add to parsley.
Add rest of ingredients; toss.
Adjust salt to taste.
Bulgur will soften after about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: In a 10-12 skillet with a tight fitting lid, brown the ground meat, stirring occasionally to break up lumps; drain off any drippings.
Spread the browned meat evenly in skillet and sprinkle half the spaghetti sauce mix.
Spoon the cottage cheese over meat; top with the uncooked noodles, the dried herbs, salt and parsley. Press down with the back of a mixing spoon.
Sprinkle evenly with the remaining dry spaghetti sauce seasoning mix.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Make pudding according to package directions.
Whip pudding, cream cheese and eggnog together and pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate least 2 hours before serving.
Sprinkle with nutmeg before serving.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Mix with a fork and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into an ungreased jelly roll pan to cover the entire bottom.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion powder and dill weed.
Spread over cooled crust.
Cover with assorted chopped vegetables (grated carrots, broccoli and cauliflower, cut in small pieces, cucumbers, green onions and ripe olives), all cut fine.
Top with grated Cheddar or white cheese.

title: layer salad
directions: Cut lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of glass pan.
Layer all other vegetables.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise; spread over the top.
Then put cheese and bacon bits on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper that has been sliced in thin strips.
Add rice, tomatoes, chili powder, hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with garden salad.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Place 3 cups lettuce in bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer eggs on top of lettuce.
Layer in order:
peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and Swiss cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top to cover to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Garnish with green onion and paprika.
Toss before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: ruth's party punch
directions: Mix in large container.
Will serve 50 people.
Very pretty to float strawberries or mint in punch bowl.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat all cake ingredients at medium speed until blended.
Pour into three (8-inch) pans.
Pans should be greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: apple cake
directions: Omit salt and soda if using self-rising flour.	Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: crumb topping
directions: With a fork, mix first 3 items.
Add flour and use hand to crumble.
Put on coffee cake (13 x 9-inch) pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
This recipe is over 100 years old.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie crust and put top crust on.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: jelly hand print
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into ball and flatten. Press handprints into dough and fill with jelly.
Bake at 375 degrees for 7-8 minutes.

title: creamy fruit frost
directions: Stir softened cream cheese into whipped topping.
Gradually add cherry fruit filling, blending well.
Fold pineapple chunks and drained oranges into cherry mixture.
Pour into 8 cup mold and freeze overnight or until firm.
Unmold and serve as salad or dessert.

title: electric skillet peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and peanuts in electric skillet.
Cook moderate boil (350° skillet setting) for 10 minutes, or until syrup is golden tan.
Stir in soda.
Pour out on baking sheet and spread thinly.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in pan; drain.
Place meat in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Tater Tots, soup, water and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with aluminum foil. Remove from oven, uncover and top with onion rings.
Bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Blend ice cream and milk on low speed of mixer.
Mix with pudding on low speed for about 2 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Let stand in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: shami
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and cook with water, 1 hour in pressure cooker or 2 hours on stovetop, over low heat.
Grind in food processor and add 1-2 eggs.
Make 2-inch balls; flatten into patties and pan-fry.

title: potato and ham soup
directions: Cover potatoes, onion and celery with water.
Cook until tender.
Add milk, butter, corn, peas, salt, pepper and ham.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Top with grated cheese and parsley.

title: easy bake cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and vanilla in a mixing bowl. Begin to blend ingredients together.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Pour mixture into unbaked crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Chill before serving. Serves 8.

title: cream-cheese mushroom rolls
directions: Chop onion finely and lightly brown in butter.
Chop mushrooms and add to onion; saute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Trim crusts from bread and roll each slice with rolling pin to flatten.
Spread mushroom mixture onto each slice and roll up.
Place, open edge, down to hold roll.
Before heating, spread rolls with soft butter.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
(Can freeze, but thaw before heating.)
Makes 96 hot appetizers.

title: magaritas
directions: Put in blender and serve.

title: fancy seasoned turkey breast(low-fat)
directions: You will need a large paper bag.

title: hearty wheat rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 1 1/2 cups whole wheat flour and 1 1/2 cups white flour in a large mixer bowl.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt in a saucepan and heat just until warm, stirring occasionally to melt shortening.
Add warm milk mixture and eggs to dry mixture in mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
(We don't recommend a hand mixer for bread.)
Scrape down sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in remaining whole wheat flour and enough remaining white flour to make a soft dough.
Knead gently just enough to incorporate flour.
Place in greased bowl, turning once.
Cover and refrigerate.
Two hours before serving, shape into rolls.
Let rise until doubled (1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with butter or margarine.
Makes 48 rolls.

title: iowa corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in a large, heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onion; saute until soft.
Add potatoes, 2 cups of the water, salt and pepper; cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn with can liquid and evaporated milk.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Beat eggs, milk and peanut butter together.
Slowly add honey and mix well.
Add flour mixture and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch oiled pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer crescent rolls as the bottom layer.
On top of rolls, spread browned and cooked sausage (crumbled).
On sausage, grate cheese.
Last, beat eggs well and pour over as final and top layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until eggs are set and well done.
Serves 6.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine and seed.
Let it cool slightly.
Put cake mix, pudding and eggs in a bowl.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: snappy turtle candies
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1 cup of frosting, crumbs, corn syrup and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until mixed, then beat two minutes at highest speed.
Set aside.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Chop onions, peppers, and garlic thin. Add to cucumbers.
Mix salt in the cucumber, onions, peppers, and garlic and add ice.
Mix well with hands.
Leave on ice for 3 hours.

title: lemon cake
directions: Put all in large bowl and mix.
Bake 35 minutes (or until top is completely set) at 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix glaze together.

title: rig taters
directions: Arrange quartered potatoes (unpeeled) in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put pats of butter all over the potatoes.
Add diced onions and green peppers over potatoes and butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil.
Spread cheese over and return to oven until melted.

title: cider punch
directions: Simmer cider or apple juice with spices in saucepan for about 15 minutes.
Cool and remove spices.
Chill juices until icy cold. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a punch bowl on block of ice. Garnish with slices of oranges and cherry halves.
Makes 5 quarts or 30 servings.

title: gulf coast barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour or until onion is tender and sauce is thickened.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and water, vinegar and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold carrots, pineapple and nuts into slightly thickened gelatin.
Turn into individual molds, pan or bowl.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash collards thoroughly.
Tear in small pieces.
Pour 3 or 4 cups of water over collards.
Put into large pot in which ham hocks have been cooking for about 30 minutes.
Cook about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: In mixer bowl, cream butter or margarine.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each addition, on medium speed of electric mixer.
Turn into pastry shell.
Chill several hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate curls, if desired.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Cook noodles.
Combine noodles, tuna, celery and green onion.
Blend sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into buttered casserole dish. Top with 1/2 zucchini.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped tomatoes.

title: hot olive sandwich loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread half of olive mixture on each bread half (French loaf, cut in half).
Top with 6 ounces thinly sliced Swiss or Jack cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut crosswise into 1 1/2-inch wide slices.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix all together dry until beads form.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until ready to roll.
Makes 4 (9 inch) crusts.

title: maple syrup barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool.
Pour mixture in blender; process until smooth.
Good for chicken.

title: honey mustard
directions: Mix all three together.
It will keep in the refrigerator for weeks.
Great as a dip on chicken strips and raw vegetables.

title: fudge-topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla; beat well.
Stir in walnuts.

title: della's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: easy lamb chop bake
directions: Best to parboil carrots while preparing rest of above. Ingredients to go into pan as listed above.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine together with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings and nuts.
(Coat nuts with flour to keep from settling to the bottom.)
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.
Top with Brown Sugar Icing.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Line onto a greased pizza pan.
Bake for 12 minutes; cool.
Cream the sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread on top of cookie crust.
Top with fruit arrangement.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Combine milk, flour and seasonings in a 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Stir in water and broth until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Meanwhile, saute onions in butter until tender, about 3 minutes. Stir onions and cooled broccoli into the thickened sauce. Gradually stir in cheese until melted, if necessary,
return to low heat to finish melting the cheese.
Do not boil.
Serve immediately.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Mix egg with milk.
Wash and dry catfish fillets.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip fillets in egg mixture, then in dry mixture.
Arrange in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with melted butter, then sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 6.

title: harvest pie
directions: Make crust according to package directions.
Bake 5 minutes at 325°.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles.
Use the jar pickles came in and add a layer of pickles, sugar and spices until jar
is full.
Store in refrigerator and shake every other day.
Ready to eat in a week to 10 days.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Pat in pan with floured hands, pressing 1/2 inch up sides of pan.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain.
Layer beef, tomatoes, and green pepper on dough.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until edges are light brown (25 to 30 minutes).
Serves 10.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Chop, boil, drain and mash eggplants.
Saute onions in margarine and add to eggplant mixture.
Mix in egg, flour and milk.
Add cheese and spices.
Place in greased baking dish.
Add rest of cheese to top, then bread crumbs and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and pour the sweetened condensed milk over cake, then
pour caramel topping over milk.
Cool and cover with Cool Whip.
Top with the crushed 5th Avenue bars.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed until stiff peak forms, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large bowl; on low speed or by hand, gradually blend in sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto wax paper.
When outside fills firm, turn over and allow to dry 12 hours.
Store in airtight container.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer beans, guacamole, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Top with green onions and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
In a bowl add 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese, 1 can mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
Beat eggs; then mix all together.
Add bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: captain billy bush's bread
directions: Scald milk and add sugar, salt and shortening.
After shortening melts, add water and cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast, softened in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Never use hot water as it kills the working power in the yeast (105° to 115°).
Add flour gradually, mixing it in thoroughly.
When dough is stiff, turn on a lightly floured board and knead until smooth and satiny.
Shape into a smooth ball; place in a greased bowl.
Cover with wax paper and a tea towel.
Let rise in a warm place until it doubles in bulk.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Melt raisin chocolate covered caramels over low heat.
Mix with whipping cream.
Spread over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Can use peanut butter chips, too.
Cut or break up to serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Gradually add sugar and continue to cream.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Beat after each egg.
Add flour gradually; add vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until cake leaves sides of pan.

title: shaker bean soup
directions: Sort and rinse beans; place in pan and cover with water.
Bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat and let stand 1 hour. Drain beans and discard liquid.
In same pan, place ham bone, 3 quarts water and beans; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add ham, onion, celery, carrots, salt, pepper and thyme. Simmer 1 hour, then add tomatoes and brown sugar.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pour into crusts.
Let chill several hours before serving.

title: irish shortbread
directions: Cream together very well the butter and sugar for 5 minutes. Should resemble whipped cream. Add flour and salt.
Dough should work up into a ball, cleaning the sides of the bowl. Press out on nonstick cookie sheet to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Run knife completely through dough as if to cut it in squares.
Pick, if desired, and sprinkle sugar, if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool, then cut following lines made before.

title: can-can fruit punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a plastic container. Cover and refrigerate.
Stir in ginger ale and serve over ice.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: quick taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef until done, along with onions; drain.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Stir taco seasoning, tomato sauce and corn and pour over hamburger. Sprinkle well with cheese.

title: guacamole(avocado salad)
directions: Pit and peel avocados.
Put in mixing bowl and mash to chunky texture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
If left to stand too long, avocados will turn brown.
For best color and flavor, you should make this salad no more than one hour before serving.

title: turkey shepherd's pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients except for pie crust, potatoes and cheese.
Fill
pie crust.

title: yogurt salad
directions: Combine yogurt to chopped vegetables.
Add salt to taste.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Put pretzels into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and sprinkle/pour over pretzels.
Bake at 300° for approximately 20 minutes.
Stir after 10 minutes.
When done, spread on brown paper bag to soak up any excess oil.
Cool and enjoy.

title: breast of chicken eden isle
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken.
Place dried beef in bottom of dish.
Place wrapped chicken breasts on top of dried beef.
Cover with mixture of soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cover slightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
When tender, remove foil and let brown slightly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well for 2 minutes.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: the most delicious pound cake
directions: In a large bowl of mixer, beat butter until creamy.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating well after each addition, until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Beat in vanilla.
Gradually and gently stir in flour, blending just until flour is thoroughly incorporated (do not overmix).

title: thick white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Reheat, stirring constantly and boil for 1 minute.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then add nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; cool.

title: aggression cookies(when the kids need to get the wiggles out!)
directions: Put in a bowl.
Wash hands super clean.
With hands mash, knead and squeeze together all the ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of glass, dip in sugar, make balls flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: the best mashed potatoes ever
directions: Place the diced potatoes in a large saucepan, cover with water and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Place potatoes in a mixer bowl.
Cut the butter and cream cheese into small pieces and add to the potatoes.
Beat with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in sour cream.
Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately or refrigerate and reheat later in a buttered casserole baked at 300° for 20 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: most popular 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat until sugar granules have dissolved and mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together in bowl.
Then add flour mixture, alternating with milk.
Beat after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into three greased 8 or 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well mixed.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.

title: old time vinegar pie
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Cook until thick, pour into baked pie shell.
Beat whites of egg until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar and spread on pie.
Place in oven and brown lightly.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan except evaporated milk.
Boil over medium heat 2 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Stir in milk.
Serve on hotcakes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in shrimp, green onions and celery to taste.
Add French dressing until dipping consistency.

title: beer biscuit
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° until done (depends on the size of muffin tins).

title: pool room slaw
directions: Mix together; bring to boil.
Put in sterilized jars and seal. Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in another bowl.
Beat into egg mixture gradually.
Stir in poppy seed and almond extract. Pour into pans.
Bake 50 to 50 minutes.

title: b. m. w. burger
directions: Mix water, soy sauce, soup mix and oil into saucepan.
Bring to full boil and add the oatmeal and walnuts.
Cook until thickened.
Set aside and cool.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cut in butter until blended. Arrange apples in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Put
dry mix over apples and extra butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, at 350° and then uncovered for 5 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or cooled with whipped cream or just plain.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together several times the flour, cocoa and the first amount of sugar.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat the egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Add second amount of sugar, two tablespoons at a time, beating on high speed until meringue holds stiff peaks.
Remainder of mixing is done by hand.
Gently fold in vanilla.
Sift flour-sugar-cocoa mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, over meringue, folding gently by hand until flour mixture disappears.
Push batter into ungreased tube pan.
Gently cut through batter with knife to remove large air bubbles.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Invert tube pan on funnel. Let hang until cake is completely cool.
To remove from pan, carefully run a knife around edge to release cake.
If desired, glaze with your favorite glaze or whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook all ingredients in a double boiler until thick.
Put in crusts. Cover with meringue and brown in oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple pie
directions: Pour mixture of egg, butter and sugar over apples and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 300°
and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: my favorite casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and salt. In 2-quart casserole, combine beef mixture, corn, tomato sauce, basil and marjoram. Cover with mashed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Arrange fruit in serving dishes.
(If fruit darkens easily, dip in orange or lemon juice.)
Top with spoonfuls of dairy sour cream or yogurt.
Sprinkle with brown sugar or drizzle with honey. Chill about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: diabetic muffins
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is absorbed.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 24 medium sized muffins.

title: smoked oyster roll
directions: Place the cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, onion and garlic salt in the bowl of a food processor and process until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain the oysters; rinse away the excess oil and pat dry.
Place in shallow bowl; mash with fork.
Spread cheese mixture into a rectangle on a piece of plastic wrap.
Spread the oysters on top of cheese, leaving 1/2-inch cheese uncovered on all sides.
Roll up, jelly-roll fashion.
Sprinkle the top of roll with minced parsley. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Great with Ritz crackers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco.
Add milk and mix well.
Add cheese and mix.
Melt margarine and cool.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Dip in melted margarine.
Place in baking pan. Bake in preheated 450° oven until brown, about 12 to 15 minutes. Makes approximately 6 (2 1/2-inch) biscuits.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add milk with flavoring added.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat well.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make hole in center of dry ingredients.
Combine the very soft butter, eggs (beaten slightly) and the milk in center of hole, too.
Stirring around from center of your mixture of dry ingredients, you will notice flour mixing into wet mixture.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 15 minutes.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet (teaspoon or tablespoon).
Makes 2 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Warm apples and put soda in apples.
Cream butter and sugar. Let apples and soda cool before adding butter, sugar and rest of the ingredients.
Preheat oven to 250° and bake for 2 hours.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 can French fried onions. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes at 350°.
Stir in remaining onions and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken nacho dip
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Fry in 2 tablespoons oil until white.
Add diced peppers.
Fry until soft.
Drain liquid.
Put in separate bowl.
Put salsa in pan with 2 cups cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add chicken and peppers.
Heat for 2 minutes.
Put chips on tray.
Put mix on top.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Blend in cornmeal.
Add oil, beaten egg and milk.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: chicken yum sticks
directions: Break wings apart and throw tips away.
Mix all ingredients and pour over wings in plastic bag or dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered in a single layer on flat cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until tender and brown.

title: snicker peanut butter cookies
directions: Choose your favorite peanut butter cookie recipe. Prepare as directed. Take a piece of dough and wrap it around 1 miniature candy bar. Repeat until dough and candy bars are used up. Place dough balls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix and let set overnight.

title: best yeast rolls
directions: Melt Crisco in 1/2 cup boiling water in large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast in 3/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add cooled Crisco. Blend egg, sugar, salt and 1/2 cup water.
Add to first mixture. Mix well.
Add flour; makes a stiff dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and knead on floured board.
Roll out 1/2 to 3/4-inches thick.
Cut and put on largest baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise 30 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Brush with melted butter again.
For cloverleaf rolls, drop 3 small balls into muffin tins to rise.

title: christmas candy pralines
directions: Mix and boil brown sugar and water until thickened stage (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: lavash hatz(armenian cracker bread)
directions: This is pretty simple bread, which is kind of a cracker, with big bubbles on it.
Every few months my grandmother would spend the day baking it and hand over a couple of shopping bags full of them to each of the families.

title: date-nut bars
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and shortening.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Blend together well; pour into greased shallow cake pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cut into bars; roll in powdered sugar.

title: roasted vegetables and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Remove any loose papery skin from garlic; separate garlic head into cloves.
In a large roasting pan (about 17 x 11 1/2-inch), place garlic cloves and chicken pieces, skin side up.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding.
Add oil, milk and eggs.
Mix well. Bake at 350° in 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans (greased and floured) until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: hamburger soup
directions: *You can use noodles or rice.
If you use rice, add 1 can of water.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until golden brown.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour on well-greased platter.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: hot tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup and milk and mix well.
If more milk is needed to thin out, add it now.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup of cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°. Pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole;
bake for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and chips and bake until cheese melts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 4 tablespoons sugar together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on top of pretzels.
Mix Jell-O and water.
Add strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: rosa's coconut sheet cake
directions: Make up cake mix by package instructions with addition of 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 package of coconut.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan by package directions.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker and butter crust into a 9 inch pie or quiche dish.
Mix 3 egg whites until fluffy and add sugar until stiff.
Mix egg yolks until thick and fold into whites.
Prepare 2 sups cool whip, 1/3 lemon juice and rind of lemon.
Fold into egg mixture.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup of graham crackers on top.
Leave in freezer overnight.

title: sauerkraut soup(kyselica)
directions: Cook potatoes in well covered water; add salt and cook until well done.
Add 1/2 cup sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons oleo.
Now, mix 2 tablespoons flour in a little water and add to the soup. Stir in 1/4 cup whipping cream.
Do not boil soup after adding the cream.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Heat
oven
to
Combine
all dry ingredients; mix well. Add
melted
butter.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down with floured fork to make crisscross. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix to good consistency for modeling.
Let children create, then gobble up.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy smooth, about 3 minutes. Blend in topping until no streaks appear. Pour into pie shell and freeze. May be topped with whipped cream and chocolate syrup.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: southern fried pies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and roll out flat.
Place saucer on dough and cut around edge of saucer.
Spoon out cooked dried apples, peaches or other fresh fruit in center of circle of dough.
Fold over and press edges together well.
Fry in deep fryer until brown.

title: asparagus frittata
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions, if frozen.
If fresh, cook in a small amount of boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain spears.
Reserve 3 spears for garnish.
Cut remaining asparagus into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside. Beat eggs until foamy.
Add cottage cheese, mustard, salt and pepper; beat and set aside.
Spray a 10-inch ovenproof skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Cook mushrooms over medium heat until tender, then stir in asparagus pieces.
Pour egg mixture over mushrooms and asparagus (put 3 reserved spears on top).
Cook mixture over low heat about 5 minutes or until mixture bubbles slightly and begins to set around the edges.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven about 10 minutes or until set.
Garnish each serving with tomato.
Serves 4.

title: "grandmama's dressing"
directions: Trim off the hard edges of cornbread and crumble it, the cornbread and the biscuits real fine.
Add chicken broth to make it about the consistency of mashed potatoes or a little thinner.
Add onion, celery, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning; taste to see if it is right and then add egg.
This will make a 9 x 13-inch pan and a smaller pan, too.
Bake at 350° or 400° until done.
Half this recipe for your family.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. Beat eggs well and mix with vanilla and fruit cocktail. Fold the fruit mixture into the dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When cool, cover with whipped topping.

title: low-fat applesauce cookies(heart healthy - 1 gram fat each)
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 6 to 8 minutes.

title: chocolate and pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together flour, crumbs, sugar and salt.
Add butter or margarine and cut in until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in 1 beaten egg.
Press evenly into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden.

title: cornbread fritters
directions: Mix meal, flour, salt and enough milk to make a stiff batter. Spoon into deep hot oil and fry on medium heat, turning once, until golden brown on both sides.

title: cookies in a jar
directions: Empty jar contents into a mixing bowl. Blend ingredients with hands. Add butter or margarine, egg and vanilla. Continue mixing with your hands until blended. Shape dough into balls and place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Makes 3 dozen.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Use pastry blender to cut margarine into coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins.
Beat eggs slightly and reserve 1 tablespoon for top of loaf.
Stir buttermilk and rest of egg into flour mixture, just until flour is moistened.
Dough will be sticky.
Turn dough onto well-floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 strokes with floured hands.
Shape dough into ball and place in a greased 2-quart round casserole.
Cut 4-inches cross about 1/4-inch deep in center.
Brush with reserved egg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread on pie pan.
Beat milk, Bisquick mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat; bake for 15 minutes.
Spread sauce on top.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and bake until knife comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Combine chili sauce, lemon juice, brown sugar, mustard, salt, Worcestershire sauce, grated onion, chili powder and water and pour over chops.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Turn once during cooking.

title: cream cheese cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 cup of the pecans. Form ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: green beans and red potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
To drippings, add onion.
Saute until tender.
Add beans and potatoes.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer about 25 to 30 minutes until beans and potatoes are tender.
Drain.
Add bacon, a little butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all together, dip into bowl and refrigerate.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: strawberry bavarian dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; stir until berries separate and gelatin begins to thicken.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into serving bowl. Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.
Makes about 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys in Proverbs 23:13-14.
Bake in a tube pan 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients into hamburger.
Warm up.
Flatten and pinch together biscuits. Spray pan with Pam.
Spread meat with ingredients over the biscuit dough.
Then spread ingredients (mushrooms, etc.) to your liking. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: noodles salad
directions: Marinate ingredients in Italian dressing for a couple of hours or overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Mix warm water and yeast. Let set 2 to 3 minutes. Mix eggs, sugar, oil and salt. Add yeast mixture, then flour. Turn out and knead. Place in greased bowl. Let rise 1 hour. Punch down. Slice or roll 2-inch balls. Place on greased pan. Let rise. Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Prepare cake and cool.
Stir pudding mix into crushed pineapple.
Prepare dessert topping according to directions.
Fold in pineapple mixture.
Frost between layers and top and sides. Garnish with sliced pineapple and maraschino cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: betty's orange jello
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Drain 1 large can of pineapple.
Let jello thicken slightly.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip (save enough Cool Whip to frost top of jello after it has hardened).
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and a little cinnamon. Refrigerate until served.

title: strawberry poke cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed in a 9 x 12 pan. Cool when done. Use end of wooden spoon and poke holes all in cake. Pour strawberries (with juice) all over top of cake, getting in each poked hole. Top with whipped topping and refrigerate.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Spread on cooled cake.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with fork; add shortening and water and let stand 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs; add vanilla, then sugar and flour beating with a fork. Add date mixture and mix to blend.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour (at least), in preheated oven.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or in slow cooker for 6 to 8 hours.

title: sweet bread dressing
directions: Cook
giblets,	backs and necks in unsalted water.
Cut up giblets,
reserving
broth,
cooked in.
Combine all other ingredients and add giblets.
Add enough broth to make mixture soupy.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in undrained pineapple; even out.
Dump in cherry pie filling; even out.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Cut oleo in patties and place on top.
Sprinkle on nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken with broccoli
directions: Cook chicken breasts in boiling water for 12 minutes.
Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Cut up cooked chicken and broccoli.
Put in shallow baking dish or casserole dish.
Add cream of chicken soup that was mixed with milk and mayonnaise. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 10 minutes more.

title: chewy ginger cookies
directions: Combine mix and sauce; blend well.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: homemade noodle soup
directions: Remove 1 to 3 cups meat from turkey carcass.
Set aside. Place turkey carcass and water in large Dutch oven; bring it to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove carcass from broth and discard.
Measure 8 cups broth and return it to Dutch oven.
Refrigerate or freeze the remainder for other uses.

title: mother's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix egg, cream sugar and flour.
Add rhubarb and raisins.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Knife should come out of custard clean.
