title: coconut orange jumbles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in coconut.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together and add alternately with orange juice to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth while adding.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet. Sprinkle with additional coconut and orange peel.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat graham crackers in bottom of pan.
Layer coconut over cracker crust, then butterscotch chips.
Next, layer chocolate chips and spoon condensed milk over top and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Will freeze well.

title: apricot-oatmeal bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the flours, salt, soda and cinnamon.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine egg, brown sugar, yogurt, water, molasses and oil.
Stir into flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats, apricots and raisins.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean; cool.

title: italian pasta fagiola soup mix
directions: To Make Jar: Rinse beans in cold water and sort out shriveled ones. Dry on paper towels overnight. Combine the spices listed. Layer the beans and spices in a Mason jar. Cut a round piece of material and add to the jar lid. Tie on your tag with these instructions:

title: mock orange julius
directions: Mix together in blender and serve.

title: tropical paradise
directions: In a blender, mix water and coconut milk with bananas on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add mango, papaya, passion fruit, guava and pineapple; mix for 1 minute.
Serve in a tall glass over chipped ice.
Makes 5 cups.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients thoroughly and
pour in greased 9
x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 30
minutes.
Bake
longer for crisp top.
Excellent with fish and also freezes well.

title: meat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered casserole.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: carrot cake(the raw one)
directions: Drain soaked ingredients; save liquid for sweetening tea, etc. Grind soaked ingredients in food processor.
Knead gently with carrots.
Add coconut and seasonings.
Mold (using a standard one or create your own), then chill overnight.

title: chicken pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with one crust.
Mix all ingredients and pour in shell.
Cover with other crust and pinch together edges. Cut slits in crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water for 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat with beater until bubbles appear.
Add 5 1/4 cups flour slowly.
Add more if needed; let rise until doubled.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll; cut in 1-inch pieces.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: no bake cherry balls
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend together sugar, butter, milk and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Chill 1 hour.
Meanwhile, drain cherries on paper towel.
Shape about 1 tablespoon coconut mixture around each cherry, leaving stem and end exposed.
Dip bottom 2/3 of cherry ball in graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate or freeze until serving.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup; add water to 280° medium crack. Add peanuts; cook 3 more minutes or until light golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add soda; remove at once from heat.
Add vanilla and butter; stir.
As soon as foaming has stopped, pour candy into greased cookie sheet with sides (thin layer).
When cool, break into pieces.
This turns out everytime.

title: ever ready bran muffins
directions: Pour water over cereal.
Add buttermilk. Cream the shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add to cooled cereal. Sift flour with soda and salt. Stir into creamed mixture only to dampen. Don't overmix.
Store in tight containers in refrigerator. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes. Mixture will keep for 3 weeks. Makes 6 dozen.

title: creamy corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Lower heat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Blend butter and flour to paste. Blend into corn.
Stir over low heat until blended.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, and pecans.
Add margarine and eggs.
Bake in an oblong pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes.
Scoop out, mash and add the cream cheese, oleo, eggs and enough milk to be of the right consistency.
Put potato mixture back into shells and top with grated cheese.
Put back in oven at 350° and heat for about 20 to 30 minutes.
These can be frozen and reheated.

title: no-salt spice blend
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Use instead of salt on vegetables, meats, hamburger or lettuce.

title: cheese-bean dip
directions: Mash avocados; stir in lemon juice, chopped tomatoes, minced onion, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Spread bean dip in a shallow 9-inch round dish.
Spread avocado mixture over bean dip. Alternate cheese over top in sections resembling pie wedges (wheelspoke fashion).
Sprinkle top with ripe olives.
Sprinkle edges with tomatoes and green onions, if desired.
Serve with king-sized chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: plantation supper
directions: Brown meat, add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in milk, soup and cream cheese until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: grandmother's hot milk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat butter and milk in a saucepan over low heat.
Beat eggs; add sugar.
Then add sifted flour; do not overbeat.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.

title: fresh broccoli with oil and lemon(microwave)
directions: Wash broccoli and discard tough portions of stalk. Split stalks lengthwise to uniform size for more even cooking. For a more tender broccoli, peel stalks with a paring knife before cooking. Arrange broccoli spears with stalks to outside of dish and flowerets in center. Add water. Cover and cook on full power 6 to 7 minutes. Let stand, covered, 3 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake a cake.
In a medium saucepan, combine pineapple with juice and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thick and syrupy.
When the cake is done, remove from oven and pierce the top with a fork (1-inch intervals).
Pour pineapple mixture over and let it cool completely.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add Eagle Brand milk with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Pour remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and make into a ball, then roll in walnuts.

title: oreo pudding(dirt cake)
directions: Crush cookies; put aside.
Mix sugar, margarine, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Then mix all together.
Layer in dish the cookies, filling, cookies, filling, etc.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: blueberry buckle coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, shortening, milk and egg; beat 30 seconds.
Carefully stir in blueberries.
Spread batter in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square or 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Sprinkle with Crumb Topping.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick test says it's done.
Drizzle with Glaze and serve warm.

title: herbed angel hair
directions: Cook the pasta until just tender; drain and return to the pot. In a medium bowl, mix the sour cream, basil, parsley, olives and chives.
Spoon over the pasta; toss to coat well.
Warm over low heat for 1 minute.
Serves 2.

title: johnson slumgullion
directions: In medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper to ground beef and cook until brown.
Add tomato paste and 1 can of water measured from tomato paste can to make sauce, then simmer as you cook macaroni in 2 1/2 cups water in saucepan for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain macaroni; combine with meat sauce.

title: fast supper
directions: Peel potatoes, slice and place in bottom of pot.
Cut up cabbage on top of potatoes.
Slice Polish sausage in half lengthwise and then in sections.
Place on top of cabbage.
Season to taste.
Add small amount of water.
Turn heat on medium and then on low.
Cook slow until cabbage and potatoes are done.

title: baked mashed potato balls
directions: Add egg yolks and parsley to mashed potatoes.
Beat egg white until stiff and fold into potato mixture.
Shape into balls.
Bake in lightly greased muffin tins or drop on a greased sheet.
Bake at 350° until crisp.
Turn to brown evenly.

title: homemade reese's peanut butter candy
directions: In a large bowl, mix well the first 4 ingredients; press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch pan (well greased).
Melt chocolate chips in microwave about 1 minute, stirring until smooth and creamy. Spread evenly.
Cover entire peanut butter mixture.
Chill.
Cut in 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: seven minute icing
directions: In top of a double boiler, mix egg whites, sugar, salt, water and corn syrup.
Beat over boiling water, at high speed, for 7 minutes or until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from water.
Add vanilla; beat 1 minute more.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix with hands.
Roll into balls.
Dip in 12 ounces milk chocolate chips, melted with 1 slab of wax.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.

title: 1-2-3 pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt together with a fork in a medium bowl.

title: toffee
directions: Cut butter into 4 pieces and add 1 at a time after each is melted.
Add sugar, water, syrup and salt.
Stir constantly.
Cook to hard crack stage (295°) or until color of brown paper bag. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet about 3/4 full.
Break up or sprinkle chocolate chips or pieces on top and spread as it melts. Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.

title: apple, celery jello salad
directions: Bring 1 cup water with red hots to a boil in the microwave, stirring every 30 seconds, approximately, until the red hots have melted.
While very hot, add the jello and stir until all is dissolved.
Add approximately 1/2 cup ice to the mixture.
Stir to cool the mixture and dissolve the ice.
When the jello is slightly thick, add the chopped apples and celery to the mixture. Refrigerate.
(Sugar-free jello doesn't set as easily as the other, so I use less water than the directions call for.)

title: chestnut dressing
directions: If using fresh chestnuts, place in a large saucepan. Cover with boiling water. Cook for 15 minutes or until tender. Cool; remove outside shell and inner skin. Chop chestnuts. Melt half of the butter in the chicken stock and wine. Melt the remaining butter in a saucepan. Saut celery and onion until soft. Cover apricots with boiling water. Cook until soft and drain. Finely chop apricots. Place the stuffing in a large bowl. Add the chestnuts, sauteed vegetables, apricots, herbs and seasonings. Add the stock mixture and toss lightly to blend. Mix in eggs, adding additional liquid if necessary.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: Combine cheese, chili and peppers in saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring often, until cheese melts.
Serve warm over chips.

title: punch
directions: Mix orange juice according to directions on can.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice and sugar to jello. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Yields 25 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Debone chicken and dice into smaller pieces.
Save chicken broth to use as liquid to mix with soups.
In a crock-pot, add rice and soup that have been mixed with 2 cans of chicken broth.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When rice looks done, add chicken and simmer until ready to eat.
Add broth as liquid, if rice and chicken get too thick.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine first
ingredients
in bowl; add buttermilk, margarine and eggs.
Beat
at low speed until moistened.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes.
Spoon batter into 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine remaining
sugar
and cinnamon;
sprinkle over batter. Cover and refrigerate 8
to
12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters(made in microwave)
directions: Combine morsels in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 3 or 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: romaine and orange salad
directions: In large bowl, combine orange peel and next 4 ingredients.
Add romaine, oranges, onion and avocado slices.
Gently toss to coat with dressing.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix milk and gelatin and cool.
Mix all the ingredients and place in a 6 qt. freezer can and fill to line with milk and freeze.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Mix, cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: salami
directions: Mix ingredients well together.
Divide in half and roll into logs.
Wrap in wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Cook on a rack over a pan of water for 3 hours at 250°.
Cool, slice thinly and serve as sandwich meat, appetizer, etc.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix and let stand 6 to 8 hours or over night. Then boil and stir for 6 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in
1 large (or 2 small) box of jello.

title: pineapple-orange congealed salad
directions: Place pineapple in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add jello, stirring until dissolved. Stir in buttermilk, coconut and pecans; cool. Fold in whipped topping; pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.

title: pecan toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar and water in a heavy pan or skillet. Start on high heat and cook on high until
it reaches soft crack stage (295°).
Stir constantly when the color begins to darken. Stir in chopped pecans and quickly pour onto large cookie sheet and spread thin.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread chocolate evenly when it's melted.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into cake pan that is greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs; combine with milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix thoroughly with milk mixture.
Heat cooking oil in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Pour desired amount of batter through funnel into hot oil, making spirals and other shapes through manipulation of the funnel.
If batter is too thick, add milk.
If too thin, add flour.
When cake is golden brown, drain on brown paper bag.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot and serve.
Choose other toppings as desired.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Place all ingredients in bowl. Do not use food processor with this recipe.
Can use 2 cans of corn if desired.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients into medium mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape into about 30 bite-size meatballs.
Place in glass baking dish; cover with wax paper.
Microwave for 8 minutes on roast; drain juice off.
Place the second group of ingredients into a 1-quart microwave dish.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes on High to cook.
Pour sauce over meatballs and continue to cook for 3 to 4 minutes on Roast or until hot.

title: pineapple thing
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cheesy potato bake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in a 12 x 12 1/2-inch baking dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover, stir and bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until done.
Stir before serving. Serves 6.

title: a mother's recipe for preserving children
directions: Mix well dogs and children.
Pour the brook over lots of pebbles.
After mixing dogs and children thoroughly, stir them around the grassy field dipping occasionally in brook, then among the flowers.
Cover at once with a crust of bright blue sky.
Bake in hot sun.
When brown, put into the bathtub to cool.
Set away between white sheets for 8 hours, sprinkling with kisses as you leave them.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water to boiling. Add walnuts and heat to boiling. Cook 1 minute. Rinse walnuts under running hot water and drain. In a large bowl, with rubber spatula, gently stir warm walnuts with sugar until sugar is dissolved. (May need to let set 5 minutes.)

title: prune cake
directions: Combine and beat on medium speed just until well blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan (greased and lightly floured).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(May be iced or glazed.)

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Melt butter and mix with crushed graham crackers.
Add crushed nuts.
Press in pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into thin strips; sprinkle with meat tenderizer. Brown in oil.
Cut green peppers into thin strips.
Add onions, garlic and celery to steak.
Saute for 2 minutes until vegetables are done.
Combine cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Add to steak. Cook until it simmers and thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Cook
bacon in a heavy iron skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper
towel.
Cook
onion	and
garlic in remaining bacon drippings
until tender.
Combine all ingredients in a lightly greased crock-pot.	Cook
on
low
for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 2 cups hot and 2 cups cold water.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.
Combine lemon jello, 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup marshmallows until melted.
Add crushed pineapple (including juice) and cream cheese.
Cool and add 1 cup Cool Whip and 1 cup salad dressing.
Chill to thicken.
Pour over lime jello; let set.
Dissolve red jello in 2 cups hot water and 2 cups cold water.
Pour over lemon jello and let set.
Serve.

title: loaded mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in pot, cover with water, boil until tender. Drain and place in mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, milk, butter salt and pepper.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in 2 c. cheese, bacon and onions.
Put in greased 3 qt. baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (set aside 1/2 cup for topping).
Add 1/4 cup melted butter to crushed Oreos. Take fork and press Oreo mix in 8-inch pie pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix 8 ounce cream cheese to 1 cup Cool Whip.
Add this mixture to pie pan.
Chill for 1 hour.
Now add prepared chocolate pudding to pie.
Chill for another hour.
Remove pie from refrigerator, spread 1 cup Cool Whip over pie.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed Oreos over and serve.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a greased and floured deep pie plate.
In a separate bowl, mix milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Pour over zucchini and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: lime jello and cottage cheese mold
directions: Mix 1st and 2nd ingredients well.
Mix lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
When dissolved, add to cottage cheese and pineapple mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use a pretty bowl.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk brownie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In a saucepan, mix the margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add the chocolate mixture to the dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix completely.
Pour into pan and bake for 25 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: chad's shipwreck casserole
directions: Brown the ground turkey (beef) and chopped onion.
Layer all the above ingredients in baking dish and cover tightly with foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
This meal is easy to put together and therefore is good for nights when you can't prepare a big meal. But it is good for hungry appetites.

title: peach-a-berry cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add fruits.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add tablespoon of butter and lemon juice.
Pour into an 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round ovenware dish.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and butter all at once.
Beat smooth.
Pour over fruit.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with cream. Serves 6.

title: red rice
directions: Saute bacon slowly and pour off part of fat.
Brown chopped onion in hot fat.
Wash rice and drain, then add it with 1 1/2 cups to tomato sauce or juice and paprika.
Pour into a lightly greased casserole and bake until rice is tender.
Gradually add tomato juice as it is absorbed.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put hamburger in bowl. Add milk, eggs, oatmeal, ketchup and A.1. sauce to hamburger. Mix into hamburger. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into baking pan. Cover top with ketchup and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender but not brown.
Add corn, broccoli, carrot and water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Stir over medium heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serves 4.

title: oven baked minestrone
directions: Use a large heavy pot with a tight fitting lid.
Set oven temperature to 350°.
Put the beef in the pot with olive oil, onion and finely chopped garlic; stir.
Brown in the oven with a cover off the pot for about 3/4 hour or until meat is well browned.
Stir several times.
Remove pot from the oven; add water, bouillon cubes, parsley and Italian seasoning.
Put cover on pot and return to oven for 1 hour.
Take pot out of oven and add all ingredients, except zucchini; stir well.
Cover and return to oven for 45 minutes.
Add sea shell macaroni; stir well.
Cover again for 1/2 hour.
Lastly, add zucchini for 1/4 hour more. Serve hot with Parmesan cheese sprinkled over the top.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Cube up bread and put in bottom of pan. Sprinkle sausage and cheese on top of it. Mix eggs, milk and mustard and pour over it. Let set overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Take a large long cake pan and put a layer of wafers, then a layer of bananas, then a layer of pineapple.
Keep on doing this until you make the cake as thick as you like.
Then put Cool Whip on top.
Crush nuts and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip and add cherries.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and rinse.
Combine with rice, tomato juice and chopped raw cabbage. Cover and cook until cabbage is tender. Add cinnamon to flavor while cooking.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake in a greased black skillet for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: scottish butter cookies
directions: Beat margarine in large bowl on high speed until light.
Add both sugars and vanilla and beat 2 minutes.
Stop mixer and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix just until combined.
Turn onto board and knead a few times to form a ball.
Place dough in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly butter baking sheets.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on baking sheets.
Dip a fork into powdered sugar and flatten each cookie slightly.
Bake until cookies are set, 12 to 15 minutes.
Leave on cookie sheets for 1 minute, then transfer to wire racks and cool completely.
Store in container with tight lid.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Or use 1 package dry Hidden Valley buttermilk dressing mix.

title: spinach and herb dip for raw vegetables
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Chill for at least 3 hours. Makes 4 cups.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and beat well. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 450° until golden brown. Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts, cool and cut or tear into pieces.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place corn chips (thin and crispy are best), then chicken in pan.
Mix onions, green chiles and tomatoes; salt and pepper as desired and pour over chicken.
Spoon sour cream over all, then shredded cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until very hot.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 375 for 1 hour or until tender. Cool. Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato and discard. Scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell. In a bowl, mash the pulp with the butter. Stir in milk, bacon, 1 c. cheese, chives, salt and pepper. Spoon into the potato shells.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Put crescent rolls flat into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Blend cream cheese with remaining ingredients.
Beat together and pour over the rolls.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375° (doesn't brown).
When it starts to crack, pull out.
When cool, sprinkle with cinnamon or top with favorite fruit.

title: apple butter pound cake
directions: Drizzle glaze mixture over cool cake.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Place turnips and onion in saucepan; cover with water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes or until turnips are tender; drain and mash.

title: shortcut barbecued chicken
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup, honey, mustard and onion powder. Arrange chicken, bone side up, on rack in broiler pan.
Brush chicken with soup mixture.
Broil 6-inches from heat for 30 minutes or until tender and juices run clear, turning once and brushing often with soup mixture during cooking.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Oil a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place 1 1/2 cups uncooked rice on the bottom.
Heat the soups with the milk.
Pour over rice.
Arrange chicken on top. Sprinkle the dry soup mix over the chicken.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Butter an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Pour mixture in.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Easy and quick.

title: chilaquiles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat; add onions and garlic.
Saute 10 minutes or until onions are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and their juice, beans, and chilies.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until juices begin to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Spread half the sauce in a 10x10x2 inch or comparable casserole.
Top with half the tortilla strips, half the sour cream and half the cheese.
Repeat second layer with remaining ingredients in same order.
Bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: 4 layer pie
directions: Crust:
Mix together melted margarine, flour and pecans and spread into a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for about 15 minutes.

title: mother's day chicken
directions: Grease a shallow baking dish and place the chicken pieces in it.
Sprinkle the onion soup mix over the chicken.
Mix mushroom soup and water and pour over chicken.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 375°.
I omit the tomatoes, but some like the tomatoes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar and cocoa in a large saucepan until it reaches 250° and stir occasionally.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour onto butter platters. Cool and cut into bite size pieces.

title: gray's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup water.
Partially thaw berries with 1 cup water.
Mix everything together and mold.

title: tuna-chip casserole
directions: Combine tuna, condensed soup, peas, celery, onion, milk and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl, mixing thoroughly.
Spoon half of tuna into a 1-quart glass casserole.
Sprinkle with half of crushed potato chips.
Spoon remaining tuna mixture into casserole and sprinkle with remaining potato chips.

title: deep south's meat pie
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Add all other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook thoroughly and let cool thoroughly before placing in dough.

title: peanut and pretzel crunch(candy)
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler; add peanuts and pretzels. Stir together until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let cool.
Pick up and store in cookie tin until ready to eat. Very good; easy to make.

title: peach tea
directions: Mix together and use 3 to 4 teaspoons in a cup of hot water. Store in airtight container.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt; stir together in cake pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and walnuts on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until cake is done.
Take cake out of oven and pour icing over cake.
While it is still hot, poke holes in the cake with fork so icing will soak down into the cake.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower for microwave
directions: Put cauliflower and water in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole with plastic wrap or glass lid.
Microwave for 9 minutes on High. Drain the liquid.
Combine the mayonnaise, onion, mustard and salt in a small bowl.
Mix well and spoon on top of the cauliflower. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on Roast power to heat topping and melt the cheese.
Let stand for 2 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan add rice, then cooked ground beef and onion.
Spread evenly into pan.
Pour beef broth and water into pan.
Cut margarine in small pieces and place on top of beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: real lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolks until slightly foamy.
Stir in 1 cup sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Now, stir in flour and salt until smooth, then pour in lemon juice and mix thoroughly. Add boiling water last.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until the filling is smooth and thick as mayonnaise (takes about 20 minutes).
Cool before pouring into pie shell. Start oven at 325° and beat up meringue, adding remaining 1/2 cup sugar when egg whites stand in peaks.
Pile meringue over pie filling and bake about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's chicken kiev
directions: Mix together the corn flakes crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic powder and the salt.
Dip chicken in melted margarine; coat in crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour wine, onions and parsley on top; bake 10 more minutes.

title: turkey and beef meatloaf
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
In the meantime, heat the sweet and sour sauce.
Spoon off excess fat.
Pour some sweet and sour sauce over loaf.
Return to oven for about 15 minutes.
Use remaining sauce for passing.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add water and mashed bananas.
Thoroughly mix in flour, soda and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crisco cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar well.
Add milk.
Beat until well mixed. Add eggs, one at a time, and cake flour slowly.
Beat well.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cooking Time: 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: classic baked pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
In a large bowl combine pasta, sauce, sausage (cooked) and 2 cups cheese.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; cover. Bake 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Uncover; top with remaining cheese and parsley.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts. Serves 12 to 15.
Super buffet item.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Use as dip for vegetables or specialty breads or spread on bagels.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and cinnamon, set aside.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add next 3 ingredients (toss).
Toast for 30 minutes at 300°.
After toasting, add brown sugar.
Divide in half.
Put bottom half in pan. Spread 1/2 gallon ice cream.
Put other 1/2 toasted mixture on top.
Put in freezer.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Break sausage into bits and brown in a skillet.
Drain well.
Then mix rice, mushrooms, soup, Worcestershire sauce, sausage and chicken.
Spoon into greased 12-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-boiled eggs in two.
Put yolks in bowl and mash with vinegar, sugar, pepper, salt and dry mustard.
Pack mixture back into eggs and sprinkle with paprika.

title: brown sugar fondant(original recipe)
directions: Lindy's, a famous New York restaurant no longer in business, was famous for it's cheesecake.
The cake is an old-fashioned one with a browned top.
It is slightly sunken, but good and solid.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, Karo, salt and milk.
Bring to a boil, then cook for 5 minutes. beat in pecans and vanilla until stiff.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Cool and cut.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Add curry to taste. Add chopped spinach.
Lay out ham slices.
Place a Swiss cheese slice onto each slice of ham.
Spread cream cheese mixture thinly onto the Swiss cheese.
Roll up as tightly as possible.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice each bundle into pieces.
Serves 12 (2 per person).

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine chocolate (melted), butter, egg, confectioners sugar and milk.
Beat until of spreading consistency.
If not thick enough, add more sugar.

title: angel food cake(this cake would melt in your mouth)
directions: Sift together flour and sugar 6 to 7 times.
Fold this into beaten egg whites a little at a time, very gently.
Add vanilla. Pour gently into angel food cake pan.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour, making sure everyone stays out of kitchen until cake is done. When done, put over 3 cups upside down to cool.

title: blackberry preserves cake
directions: Mix.
Put in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350°.
Bake until done.

title: caesar's salad
directions: Pour over beans.
When ready to serve, not before, shake dressing and pour over greens.
Slightly beat one whole egg and pour over everything.
Toss until all greens are coated and no raw egg shows.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Prepare the vegetables according to package; drain.
Put bread in blender.
Blend into coarse crumbs and set aside.
Put milk, cheese, flour and salt in blender; blend until smooth.
Combine broccoli and eggs.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Combine butter and crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: linda's oriental spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and place in large bowl.
Toss with soy sauce.
In large frying pan or wok, heat 1 tablespoon peanut oil.
Add ginger, garlic and meat. Stir-fry until cooked.
Remove and add to spaghetti.
Add remaining tablespoon of oil to pan and add vegetables.
Stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Toss meat and vegetables with spaghetti. Serve a bit warm or at room temperature.
Serves 6 hungry people.

title: pecan pie 4
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour and beaten eggs.
Add salt and syrup.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Blend well.
Makes enough for 3 ready made pie crusts.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown and crumble sausage; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt Velveeta cheese.
Add enough milk to thin down.
Mix sausage and place in crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve with Fritos.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine blackberry jello and 2 cups hot water. Chill for 30 minutes. Add the pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let jell.
Beat together the sour cream, cream cheese and sugar. Stir in the Cool Whip, pecans and vanilla. Spread on top of jello. Store in refrigerator until serving.

title: 9 day pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in hot water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Soak 24 hours.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: Melt oleo in a 1-quart casserole in microwave.
Mix other ingredients well and add to oleo.
Cook, covered, for 8 minutes or until pudding is slightly soft in the center, stirring 1 time. Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green rice
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter.
When almost done, add broccoli and mushrooms.
Cook rice about 1/2 done.
Mix all together with mushroom soup and pour in a dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: nana's meat balls
directions: Soak bread in a little water and squeeze out good or use bread crumbs soaked in 1/4 cup milk.
Mix ground meat, pepper, salt, bread or bread crumbs, beaten egg, onion and Lea & Perrins together well.
Form into small balls and roll in flour twice. Brown in greased skillet, then pour water over all; stir.
Place mixture in casserole and bake in oven for 30 minutes at 375°. Remove from oven and add mushrooms.
Can use mushroom juice if needed.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes more.

title: date or raisin bars
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to bubble, then cool and set aside.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, soup and preserves together. Put chicken breasts in large baking dish skin side up. Cover with mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mother's sugar cookies
directions: Put soda into flour.
Cream together sugars and lard.
Add beaten eggs, milk, flour and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make a dough that can be rolled out and cut.
(Sometimes I add a tablespoon of vanilla.)
Sprinkle sugar on cookies and some nuts, if you have them.

title: potato corn fritters
directions: Combine and serve with fritters.

title: cube steak rolls-italian style(serves 8)
directions: Season the 8 steaks with salt and pepper. Clean mushrooms. Chop fine.
Saute in 2 tablespoons of oil for a few minutes. Remove from heat. Mince parsley, slice onions and add cheese.
Add to mushrooms and mix.
Evenly divide mix over 8 steaks and spread out.
Roll steaks and tie with string. Brown on all sides in oil. Drain off the excess oil. Pour tomatoes over rolls.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until
meat is tender.
Put meat on platter (heated).
Blend cornstarch with water.
Add to tomato mix.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over meat.
Serve with pasta or rice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, eggs and milk.
Cook until thick. Take off stove; stir in vanilla and butter.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Makes 1 pie.

title: another angel delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add thawed strawberries and stir to mix berries. Place wide end of cake down on serving plate. Cut 1-inch layer from top and set aside. Dig center out 1-inch from sides and bottom. Remove cake sections, tearing to small pieces. Fold pieces into strawberry mixture. Pour into cake shell. Place cake layer on top. Whip cream until thick and stir in sugar or use Cool Whip and sugar. Spread over top and sides of cake. Decorate with whole strawberries. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: maw maw katie's cheese ball
directions: Mix at room temperature by hand.
Roll into ball.
Reserve enough chipped beef to cover outside of ball.
Serve on a platter surrounded by Ritz crackers.
